1
00:00:14,473 --> 00:00:16,475
[♪ Melancholic music playing]

2
00:01:07,698 --> 00:01:13,329
Okay. How about...
a rocket dog with space chips?

3
00:01:14,831 --> 00:01:16,541
Spaghetti with meteors?

4
00:01:18,501 --> 00:01:20,211
Galactic grape cup?

5
00:01:20,711 --> 00:01:21,754
[sighs]

6
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:24,757
Elio, you have
to eat something.

7
00:01:26,050 --> 00:01:28,386
Do you remember what your mom
used to order for you?

8
00:01:29,929 --> 00:01:31,264
[sighs]

9
00:01:32,223 --> 00:01:34,517
[friend] Major Solís,
what are you doing here?

10
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,687
[Solís] Hey!
Yeah, I-I'm with my nephew.

11
00:01:37,770 --> 00:01:39,522
I'm trying to get him to eat.

12
00:01:39,605 --> 00:01:42,650
[friend]
Oh, right. Your nephew.

13
00:01:43,192 --> 00:01:47,196
I heard about your brother
and his wife. I'm so sorry.

14
00:01:47,280 --> 00:01:48,281
[Solís] Thank you.

15
00:01:49,366 --> 00:01:50,825
We're managing.

16
00:01:50,909 --> 00:01:53,036
[friend] What about
the astronaut program?

17
00:01:53,119 --> 00:01:55,163
- Weren't you about...
- [Solís] No. Not anymore.

18
00:01:55,246 --> 00:01:57,791
The, um--
The timing just isn't right.

19
00:01:57,874 --> 00:01:58,875
[friend] Of course.

20
00:01:59,459 --> 00:02:01,086
But it's-- But it's been great

21
00:02:01,169 --> 00:02:02,921
spending time
with my new roommate.

22
00:02:03,004 --> 00:02:04,005
Right, buddy?

23
00:02:04,089 --> 00:02:05,882
[gasps] Oh, no.

24
00:02:05,966 --> 00:02:07,968
[indistinct excited chatter]

25
00:02:11,596 --> 00:02:12,681
[laughs]

26
00:02:26,782 --> 00:02:28,784
[♪ Mysterious music playing]

27
00:02:48,853 --> 00:02:51,021
[recording speaking Spanish]

28
00:02:51,105 --> 00:02:53,065
[recording speaking Italian]

29
00:02:53,941 --> 00:02:56,861
[child's voice] <i>Hello from
the children of Planet Earth.</i>

30
00:03:00,114 --> 00:03:01,782
[museum narrator]
<i>Since the dawn of time,</i>

31
00:03:01,866 --> 00:03:04,910
<i>humans have gazed at the stars
and wondered...</i>

32
00:03:05,494 --> 00:03:06,954
<i>are we alone?</i>

33
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:10,457
Voyager <i>is our attempt
to find out.</i>

34
00:03:11,375 --> 00:03:14,336
<i>This intrepid explorer is
on a mission,</i>

35
00:03:14,420 --> 00:03:18,090
<i>traveling farther
than any human has ever gone,</i>

36
00:03:18,173 --> 00:03:22,094
<i>to the distant reaches
of the cosmos and beyond.</i>

37
00:03:23,679 --> 00:03:27,182
Voyager <i>will never see those
who made it again.</i>

38
00:03:27,266 --> 00:03:31,312
<i>It will drift on,
solitary and alone.</i>

39
00:03:32,146 --> 00:03:33,898
<i>But maybe one day,</i>

40
00:03:33,981 --> 00:03:36,734
<i>distant worlds
will receive its message</i>

41
00:03:36,817 --> 00:03:39,361
<i>and Voyager
will complete its mission,</i>

42
00:03:39,445 --> 00:03:42,781
<i>proving we aren't so alone
after all.</i>

43
00:03:48,746 --> 00:03:51,040
[Solís] Elio! Elio!

44
00:03:51,540 --> 00:03:53,626
[sighs] Elio...

45
00:03:53,709 --> 00:03:56,128
Are you-- Are you hurt?
What happened?

46
00:03:56,211 --> 00:03:57,338
What happened?

47
00:03:57,421 --> 00:03:59,423
Is life really out there,
<i>Tía</i> Olga?

48
00:03:59,506 --> 00:04:00,507
What?

49
00:04:00,765 --> 00:04:02,016
[Olga stammers]

50
00:04:02,100 --> 00:04:03,101
Come on.

51
00:04:03,977 --> 00:04:06,771
You can't run away
like that, Elio.

52
00:04:12,443 --> 00:04:14,696
[Voyager recording
speaking Serbian]

53
00:04:14,779 --> 00:04:15,947
[Voyager recording
speaking Dutch]

54
00:04:16,030 --> 00:04:17,657
[recording] <i>I would like
to extend the greetings</i>

55
00:04:17,740 --> 00:04:19,325
<i>of the government
and the people of Canada.</i>

56
00:04:19,409 --> 00:04:22,203
[overlapping
Voyager recordings]

57
00:04:32,130 --> 00:04:34,174
[recordings continue]

58
00:04:48,813 --> 00:04:51,900
[child's voice] <i>Hello from
the children of Planet Earth.</i>

59
00:05:21,721 --> 00:05:23,681
[tuning feedback]

60
00:05:29,270 --> 00:05:30,271
Oh, wait.

61
00:05:31,606 --> 00:05:33,399
- [zipper closes]
- [sighs]

62
00:05:37,528 --> 00:05:38,529
Okay.

63
00:05:38,613 --> 00:05:41,991
[♪ Talking Heads
"Once in a Lifetime" playing]

64
00:06:05,306 --> 00:06:06,307
Elio!

65
00:06:06,307 --> 00:06:36,307
<b>Subtitle | www.movieddl.me</b>

66
00:06:56,992 --> 00:06:59,369
[snores]

67
00:07:01,997 --> 00:07:03,957
- [♪ Mysterious music playing]
- Huh?

68
00:07:07,210 --> 00:07:08,462
[gasps]

69
00:07:09,713 --> 00:07:11,298
[♪ Music crescendoes]

70
00:07:12,549 --> 00:07:13,967
- Hey.
- [exclaims]

71
00:07:14,050 --> 00:07:14,926
[both groan]

72
00:07:15,427 --> 00:07:17,137
Are you Elio?

73
00:07:17,220 --> 00:07:18,847
Who wants to know?

74
00:07:18,930 --> 00:07:21,224
You put flyers up
for a Ham Radio Club?

75
00:07:21,308 --> 00:07:22,350
Uh... [chuckles]

76
00:07:22,434 --> 00:07:24,728
Uh, I-I am Elio Solís,

77
00:07:24,811 --> 00:07:28,023
president and leader
of the Ham Radio Club

78
00:07:28,106 --> 00:07:29,900
of this beach.

79
00:07:29,983 --> 00:07:31,151
Cool. I'm Bryce.

80
00:07:31,234 --> 00:07:32,903
Great, cool, awesome.
Did you bring it?

81
00:07:32,986 --> 00:07:34,029
Oh-Oh, yeah.

82
00:07:34,112 --> 00:07:36,740
It's my dad's ham radio,
but I have my own call sign.

83
00:07:36,823 --> 00:07:38,408
It's PXLOL... [chuckles]

84
00:07:38,492 --> 00:07:41,203
...which sometimes
makes people I talk to laugh.

85
00:07:41,787 --> 00:07:42,871
How far have you called?

86
00:07:42,954 --> 00:07:45,415
On Friday I talked to...

87
00:07:46,208 --> 00:07:47,375
Ohio.

88
00:07:47,459 --> 00:07:48,335
Oh.

89
00:07:48,835 --> 00:07:51,671
If I can pair these together,
I can double their reach.

90
00:07:51,755 --> 00:07:53,131
Okay, you can go now.

91
00:07:53,215 --> 00:07:54,716
Go? Wait.

92
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,092
Where's everyone else?

93
00:07:56,176 --> 00:07:59,638
Unfortunately, most of our
members came down with, uh...

94
00:07:59,721 --> 00:08:01,681
amnesia and forgot to come,

95
00:08:01,765 --> 00:08:03,475
but I'll see you at the
next meetup in three months!

96
00:08:03,558 --> 00:08:04,976
- What's up, Bryce?
- Hey.

97
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:06,520
Oh. Oh. Oh.

98
00:08:06,603 --> 00:08:08,355
- One, two...
- [Bryce's friend] Oh.

99
00:08:08,855 --> 00:08:10,065
[Bryce]
You almost messed up there.

100
00:08:10,148 --> 00:08:11,149
Hey. Uh...

101
00:08:11,233 --> 00:08:12,442
- [Bryce] Uh-huh.
- Oh.

102
00:08:12,526 --> 00:08:13,693
[Bryce] Oh, yeah.

103
00:08:13,777 --> 00:08:15,278
- Swoosh!
- Nice. [chuckles]

104
00:08:15,362 --> 00:08:17,322
This is Caleb.
He wanted to come too.

105
00:08:17,405 --> 00:08:19,115
Oh. Hey.

106
00:08:19,199 --> 00:08:20,367
What's with the hat?

107
00:08:20,450 --> 00:08:21,618
Uh... [clears throat]

108
00:08:21,701 --> 00:08:23,870
Like I said,
the meetup's been postponed.

109
00:08:23,954 --> 00:08:25,121
Shingles is no joke.

110
00:08:25,205 --> 00:08:26,706
I thought it was amnesia.

111
00:08:26,790 --> 00:08:28,792
Oh, my gosh, you're right.
It's spreading.

112
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:30,293
You better go
before you catch it. Bye!

113
00:08:30,377 --> 00:08:32,295
- Yo, what's up with this guy?
- Dude, chill.

114
00:08:32,379 --> 00:08:33,588
[Bryce] He's the kid
whose parents died.

115
00:08:33,672 --> 00:08:35,173
Hey, that's
classified information.

116
00:08:35,257 --> 00:08:37,008
As leader of this radio club,
I hereby...

117
00:08:37,092 --> 00:08:39,636
- [mysterious sounds playing]
- [Elio gasps]

118
00:08:39,719 --> 00:08:40,679
- Whoa.
- Did you do that?

119
00:08:40,762 --> 00:08:41,721
Shh, shh, shh.

120
00:08:41,805 --> 00:08:42,639
No.

121
00:08:42,722 --> 00:08:44,432
- Is this supposed to happen?
- Don't. Stop it!

122
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:46,768
Hello? Hello? Can you hear me?

123
00:08:46,852 --> 00:08:48,103
- Let me see that.
- Don't touch that.

124
00:08:48,186 --> 00:08:50,647
- I was just looking at it.
- I have to respond.

125
00:08:50,730 --> 00:08:51,565
- Let go!
- Quit it.

126
00:08:52,107 --> 00:08:53,650
[groans] No!

127
00:08:54,568 --> 00:08:55,569
[mysterious sounds stop]

128
00:08:55,652 --> 00:08:58,280
- [gasps]
- Yo, that was not my fault.

129
00:08:58,363 --> 00:08:59,614
- I-I didn't mean to...
- [growls]

130
00:08:59,698 --> 00:09:01,199
- Uh...
- Oh, come on.

131
00:09:01,283 --> 00:09:03,535
You suborbital, gaseous...

132
00:09:03,618 --> 00:09:05,161
waste of mass!

133
00:09:05,245 --> 00:09:07,622
- Whoa.
- Activate supernova blast!

134
00:09:07,706 --> 00:09:09,833
[Caleb] Get off of me,
you little freak.

135
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,960
- Come on, guys, stop!
- [Caleb] He bit me!

136
00:09:12,043 --> 00:09:14,504
Hey, what are you doing?

137
00:09:14,588 --> 00:09:15,964
[Elio snarls]

138
00:09:16,214 --> 00:09:18,216
Unbelievable!

139
00:09:18,300 --> 00:09:21,052
Fighting on the beach,
skipping school?

140
00:09:21,136 --> 00:09:22,971
Am I going to have to put
a tracker on you?

141
00:09:23,054 --> 00:09:24,180
- [Olga sighs]
- [Caleb grunts]

142
00:09:24,264 --> 00:09:26,349
[Olga]Now your eye. <i>Ay Mamá.</i>

143
00:09:26,433 --> 00:09:29,019
The doctor said not
to touch it for two weeks.

144
00:09:29,102 --> 00:09:30,312
- Elio!
- Oh.

145
00:09:30,395 --> 00:09:31,479
You meant starting now.

146
00:09:31,563 --> 00:09:34,107
This is serious!
What were you thinking?

147
00:09:34,190 --> 00:09:36,693
I was minding my own business,
taking in the night air

148
00:09:36,776 --> 00:09:38,445
and suddenly these ruffians
attacked me.

149
00:09:38,528 --> 00:09:39,571
No, no, no.

150
00:09:39,654 --> 00:09:40,614
Look at me in the eye

151
00:09:40,697 --> 00:09:42,532
and for once,
tell me the truth.

152
00:09:44,627 --> 00:09:45,920
[speaking other language]

153
00:09:46,003 --> 00:09:47,797
No. I'm not learning Elioese.

154
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:49,131
[speaking Elioese]

155
00:09:49,215 --> 00:09:50,466
[chuckles, growls]

156
00:09:50,550 --> 00:09:51,509
Major Solís.

157
00:09:51,592 --> 00:09:53,094
You going
to the seminar tonight?

158
00:09:53,177 --> 00:09:56,097
There'll be a speaker from the
Astronaut Selection Program.

159
00:09:56,180 --> 00:09:57,098
[sighs]

160
00:09:57,181 --> 00:09:58,516
No. No, no.

161
00:09:58,599 --> 00:09:59,851
Something came up.

162
00:09:59,934 --> 00:10:01,644
[friend]
Oh, is this the nephew

163
00:10:01,727 --> 00:10:02,728
we've heard so much about?

164
00:10:02,812 --> 00:10:03,896
Yes, that's him.

165
00:10:03,980 --> 00:10:05,314
- <i>Gloodle!</i>
- Stop it!

166
00:10:06,274 --> 00:10:08,484
I don't know
if this is boundary testing...

167
00:10:08,568 --> 00:10:09,944
...or sleep regression, or...
[groans]

168
00:10:10,528 --> 00:10:12,655
Which one of these is you?

169
00:10:13,239 --> 00:10:16,659
I don't know,
but I think that one is you.

170
00:10:17,285 --> 00:10:18,369
[muffled screech]

171
00:10:19,328 --> 00:10:21,581
Okay, I've got
one last meeting.

172
00:10:21,664 --> 00:10:23,541
So, I need you to sit here

173
00:10:23,624 --> 00:10:25,251
and not move or speak

174
00:10:25,334 --> 00:10:27,753
or injure yourself
for ten minutes.

175
00:10:29,255 --> 00:10:30,298
[sighs]

176
00:10:30,381 --> 00:10:32,592
I have enough
to deal with already.

177
00:10:35,511 --> 00:10:36,846
[sighs]

178
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,973
[soldier] What's with
this emergency meeting?

179
00:10:39,056 --> 00:10:40,182
Oh, you didn't hear?

180
00:10:40,266 --> 00:10:42,351
Melmac thinks he found aliens.

181
00:10:42,435 --> 00:10:44,687
[soldier chuckles]
This ought to be good.

182
00:10:47,064 --> 00:10:48,441
[indistinct whispering]

183
00:10:49,317 --> 00:10:51,360
All right, Mr. Melmac,
let's hear it.

184
00:10:52,028 --> 00:10:53,654
Major... [winces]

185
00:10:53,738 --> 00:10:55,239
Major Solís, earlier today,

186
00:10:55,323 --> 00:10:58,326
I found this signal coming
from interstellar space.

187
00:10:58,409 --> 00:11:01,245
[mysterious sounds playing]

188
00:11:09,378 --> 00:11:10,630
[Olga] Melmac, please.

189
00:11:10,713 --> 00:11:12,214
- It's late...
- Wait, wait, wait.

190
00:11:12,298 --> 00:11:13,799
Listen closely.

191
00:11:15,927 --> 00:11:17,762
[child's voice, distorted]
<i>Hello, Planet Earth.</i>

192
00:11:17,845 --> 00:11:20,139
<i>Hello, Planet Earth.</i>

193
00:11:20,222 --> 00:11:22,224
In 1977, NASA launched the...

194
00:11:22,308 --> 00:11:23,809
- The Golden Record.
- The Golden Record! Yes.

195
00:11:23,893 --> 00:11:26,938
- The what?
- The Golden Record, sir,

196
00:11:27,021 --> 00:11:28,522
was Earth's
message in a bottle.

197
00:11:28,606 --> 00:11:31,192
[child's voice] <i>Hello from
the children of Planet Earth.</i>

198
00:11:31,275 --> 00:11:32,276
Don't you see?

199
00:11:32,360 --> 00:11:34,070
[child's voice, distorted]
<i>Hello, Planet Earth.</i>

200
00:11:34,153 --> 00:11:35,863
I think someone
in interstellar space

201
00:11:35,947 --> 00:11:37,907
found our message
and is sending it back to us

202
00:11:37,990 --> 00:11:38,950
as a reply!

203
00:11:39,784 --> 00:11:41,035
- Melmac...
- Major...

204
00:11:41,118 --> 00:11:42,495
- Melmac...
- Major!

205
00:11:42,578 --> 00:11:45,039
We can't just leave it
like this, we have to respond.

206
00:11:45,122 --> 00:11:46,791
I've already rerouted
every satellite

207
00:11:46,874 --> 00:11:47,875
to send the signal back.

208
00:11:47,959 --> 00:11:49,835
Sure, it might cause
a few system failures.

209
00:11:49,919 --> 00:11:51,837
Whoop. Sorry.
Maybe a small electrical fire,

210
00:11:51,921 --> 00:11:55,341
but it would be worth it
for first contact!

211
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:58,552
I have everything cued up
and ready to go.

212
00:11:58,636 --> 00:12:00,262
Just say the word!

213
00:12:00,346 --> 00:12:04,058
If someone or something
is calling out to Earth,

214
00:12:04,141 --> 00:12:07,395
who on Earth do you want
taking that call?

215
00:12:12,233 --> 00:12:13,651
- You...
- [gasps]

216
00:12:13,734 --> 00:12:15,277
- ...should go home.
- Oh.

217
00:12:15,361 --> 00:12:16,988
- Take a week.
- [soldier] Take two weeks.

218
00:12:17,071 --> 00:12:18,072
No. You got to believe me.

219
00:12:18,155 --> 00:12:19,657
Major, please!
They're out there!

220
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:20,908
Major! [screams] Unhand me!

221
00:12:20,992 --> 00:12:25,287
[sighs] May I remind everyone
that we are orbital analysts.

222
00:12:25,371 --> 00:12:28,582
We track space debris,
not rogue UFO signals.

223
00:12:29,291 --> 00:12:31,711
Let's just... [sighs]

224
00:12:32,211 --> 00:12:33,504
Let's just take five.

225
00:12:33,587 --> 00:12:34,797
It's been a long night.

226
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:37,049
What a nut job.

227
00:12:37,883 --> 00:12:39,385
[♪ Tense music playing]

228
00:12:51,397 --> 00:12:55,026
This is Elio Solís
of the planet Earth. Uh...

229
00:12:55,526 --> 00:12:57,611
I come in peace...

230
00:12:57,695 --> 00:13:00,406
and I'm super excited
to join you. Uh...

231
00:13:00,489 --> 00:13:02,533
I'm creative, hardworking...

232
00:13:03,451 --> 00:13:04,702
shredded.

233
00:13:04,785 --> 00:13:06,787
Uh, so please come and get me.
I'll be waiting.

234
00:13:06,871 --> 00:13:07,997
Okay, bye. Love you.

235
00:13:11,625 --> 00:13:12,752
Yes.

236
00:13:13,961 --> 00:13:15,087
Yes!

237
00:13:16,672 --> 00:13:17,631
Yes!

238
00:13:19,592 --> 00:13:20,426
[exclaims]

239
00:13:20,509 --> 00:13:21,469
[chuckles]

240
00:13:25,811 --> 00:13:26,812
[Olga] Oh, no.

241
00:13:27,104 --> 00:13:29,356
Time is of the essence.
They could be here any minute.

242
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:30,315
I got to pack!

243
00:13:30,399 --> 00:13:31,567
I take full responsibility,

244
00:13:31,650 --> 00:13:33,736
but... [chuckles] ...I mean,
you have kids, right?

245
00:13:33,819 --> 00:13:35,320
I'll be out of your way soon.
Don't worry.

246
00:13:35,404 --> 00:13:36,655
Just need a few snacks
for the road.

247
00:13:36,739 --> 00:13:37,573
Elio!

248
00:13:37,656 --> 00:13:38,615
Sorry, ma'am. What was that?

249
00:13:38,699 --> 00:13:40,242
Which flavor will you
miss the least? <i>¿Fuego?</i>

250
00:13:40,325 --> 00:13:41,326
- <i>Fuego.</i> Yeah.
- I-I understand.

251
00:13:41,410 --> 00:13:43,328
Should I bring forks, or would
they think they're weapons?

252
00:13:43,412 --> 00:13:45,205
Not worth the risk!
I'll bring spoons.

253
00:13:45,289 --> 00:13:47,291
Nice, peaceful spoons.

254
00:13:47,374 --> 00:13:48,959
- Where's my good cape?
- You too, ma'am.

255
00:13:49,043 --> 00:13:50,627
- It's not in the wash, is it?
- Thank you.

256
00:13:51,128 --> 00:13:52,421
- Ah. Here it is!
- Elio...

257
00:13:52,504 --> 00:13:54,673
Blue or green? Which one says,
"Take me with you,"

258
00:13:54,757 --> 00:13:55,758
but not in a desperate way?

259
00:13:55,841 --> 00:13:57,134
Elio, stop! Please!

260
00:13:59,219 --> 00:14:01,263
Aliens are not coming for you.

261
00:14:02,431 --> 00:14:03,515
But that guy said...

262
00:14:03,599 --> 00:14:05,684
You're out of control.
You got in a fight.

263
00:14:05,768 --> 00:14:07,978
You shut down power
to the whole base

264
00:14:08,062 --> 00:14:09,980
and I almost lost my job!

265
00:14:10,481 --> 00:14:11,732
[Olga sighs]

266
00:14:12,649 --> 00:14:14,026
We have to try
something different.

267
00:14:16,533 --> 00:14:18,201
Boarding school? You're trying
to get rid of me.

268
00:14:18,285 --> 00:14:20,620
No, this is just
their sleep away camp.

269
00:14:20,704 --> 00:14:21,705
It's just a couple of weeks.

270
00:14:21,788 --> 00:14:23,081
I can't go.
They're coming tonight.

271
00:14:23,165 --> 00:14:25,792
You need to make friends
or just a friend.

272
00:14:25,876 --> 00:14:28,086
I don't care about friends.
I need to meet aliens.

273
00:14:28,170 --> 00:14:29,171
Why?

274
00:14:29,254 --> 00:14:31,923
Because there's 500 million
habitable planets out there

275
00:14:32,007 --> 00:14:33,467
and one of them's
got to want me!

276
00:14:33,550 --> 00:14:35,218
Because obviously you don't!

277
00:14:35,302 --> 00:14:37,179
Of course, I do! We're family!

278
00:14:37,262 --> 00:14:38,889
You're not my family!

279
00:14:49,566 --> 00:14:50,567
[sighs]

280
00:14:50,650 --> 00:14:52,360
Your life isn't
up there, Elio.

281
00:14:53,570 --> 00:14:54,905
It's down here.

282
00:14:59,205 --> 00:15:00,456
[grunts]

283
00:15:13,260 --> 00:15:15,429
[Olga]
I-I can't deal with this.

284
00:15:15,513 --> 00:15:17,807
I don't know if anybody
can deal with this.

285
00:15:18,307 --> 00:15:19,725
[sighs]

286
00:15:20,226 --> 00:15:21,435
When I drop him <i>off</i> tomorrow,

287
00:15:21,519 --> 00:15:23,562
I'm going to see if they can
enroll him in the fall.

288
00:15:24,730 --> 00:15:25,731
I know,

289
00:15:25,815 --> 00:15:30,653
but this just isn't how
I thought my life would be.

290
00:15:35,616 --> 00:15:37,118
[narrator on recording]
<i>It's an ancient human theme.</i>

291
00:15:37,201 --> 00:15:39,286
<i>You can find it
in virtually every culture,</i>

292
00:15:39,370 --> 00:15:41,789
<i>in, uh, religion,
folklore, superstition</i>

293
00:15:41,872 --> 00:15:43,499
- <i>and now in science.</i>
- [Elio crying]

294
00:15:43,582 --> 00:15:47,461
<i>The search for life elsewhere
is remarkable in our age,</i>

295
00:15:47,545 --> 00:15:48,879
<i>because this is the first time</i>

296
00:15:48,963 --> 00:15:52,049
<i>that we can actually do
something besides speculation.</i>

297
00:15:53,134 --> 00:15:55,386
<i>We can send spacecraft
to nearby planets.</i>

298
00:15:56,804 --> 00:15:58,431
<i>We can use
large radio telescopes</i>

299
00:15:58,514 --> 00:16:02,143
<i>to see if there is any message
being sent to us lately...</i>

300
00:16:03,060 --> 00:16:06,397
<i>and it touches to the deepest
of human concerns.</i>

301
00:16:07,732 --> 00:16:08,858
<i>Are we alone?</i>

302
00:16:25,926 --> 00:16:27,052
[whistle blows]

303
00:16:29,596 --> 00:16:31,056
[camper]
No contact! No contact!

304
00:16:31,399 --> 00:16:32,400
[whistle blows]

305
00:16:32,483 --> 00:16:35,069
[Olga] You know I went here,
too, when I was a kid.

306
00:16:35,945 --> 00:16:37,697
You might not believe me
right now...

307
00:16:39,031 --> 00:16:40,450
but this will be good for you.

308
00:16:46,789 --> 00:16:47,623
Oh.

309
00:16:47,707 --> 00:16:49,375
Counselor Truman,
could I have a word?

310
00:16:49,459 --> 00:16:50,585
Of course, Major.

311
00:16:54,213 --> 00:16:55,047
[gasps]

312
00:16:56,257 --> 00:16:58,050
We got in so much trouble...

313
00:17:00,096 --> 00:17:01,389
because of you.

314
00:17:01,472 --> 00:17:02,556
Yeah. Thanks a lot.

315
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:03,724
- [Caleb grunts]
- [exclaims]

316
00:17:03,808 --> 00:17:05,226
[Caleb]
Better watch your back.

317
00:17:05,309 --> 00:17:06,435
- Yeah.
- [sighs]

318
00:17:07,728 --> 00:17:09,605
[thunder rumbling]

319
00:17:10,773 --> 00:17:12,608
[static on Ham radio]

320
00:17:15,277 --> 00:17:16,278
Ugh.

321
00:17:17,238 --> 00:17:18,239
[sighs]

322
00:17:19,450 --> 00:17:20,910
[Caleb] He's going to be
so freaked out!

323
00:17:20,994 --> 00:17:22,704
[Bryce] Shh. Follow my lead.

324
00:17:22,787 --> 00:17:24,122
- [Caleb giggling]
- [camper] Shh, shh.

325
00:17:24,205 --> 00:17:25,623
Quiet. Quiet.

326
00:17:25,707 --> 00:17:27,041
We're not going to
hurt him, right?

327
00:17:27,125 --> 00:17:29,043
- Just scare him a little?
- Come on, it'll be funny.

328
00:17:29,127 --> 00:17:30,128
[gasps]

329
00:17:31,546 --> 00:17:33,298
- [campers chuckling]
- Shut up! You'll wake him up.

330
00:17:33,381 --> 00:17:35,258
- [Caleb] Come on.
- [camper] Quiet, quiet!

331
00:17:35,341 --> 00:17:36,718
- [camper] Shh, shh, shh.
- [thunderclap]

332
00:17:36,801 --> 00:17:38,303
[gasps]

333
00:17:38,386 --> 00:17:39,721
[Caleb] Greetings, Earthling.

334
00:17:39,804 --> 00:17:41,514
We come in peace!

335
00:17:42,765 --> 00:17:43,850
[Bryce] Where did he go?

336
00:17:46,269 --> 00:17:48,104
[panting]

337
00:17:50,983 --> 00:17:52,443
<i>Athena 5,</i> there is
a decommissioned satellite

338
00:17:52,526 --> 00:17:53,569
headed your way.

339
00:17:53,652 --> 00:17:56,113
I'm calculating a new
flight path for you. Standby.

340
00:17:56,196 --> 00:17:57,698
- [beeping]
- [astronaut] <i>Go ahead, Montez.</i>

341
00:17:57,781 --> 00:18:00,117
Minus 53, plus 32, roll seven.

342
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:01,577
[astronaut] <i>Yeah, copy that.</i>

343
00:18:03,162 --> 00:18:04,246
[Olga] Sorry about the scare.

344
00:18:04,330 --> 00:18:06,373
There's been a lot of
satellite interference today.

345
00:18:06,457 --> 00:18:08,709
[astronaut] <i>Roger that.</i>
Athena 5, <i>over and out.</i>

346
00:18:12,463 --> 00:18:13,714
[sighs]

347
00:18:22,222 --> 00:18:24,141
[pulsing]

348
00:18:30,189 --> 00:18:32,399
[whirring]

349
00:18:32,483 --> 00:18:33,692
[static on radio]

350
00:18:33,776 --> 00:18:36,695
[musical notes playing]

351
00:18:36,779 --> 00:18:40,032
- [interference]
- [musical notes continue]

352
00:18:40,115 --> 00:18:42,409
[bleeping]

353
00:18:43,786 --> 00:18:45,162
Uh...

354
00:18:48,707 --> 00:18:49,958
[gasps]

355
00:18:52,086 --> 00:18:53,670
[Caleb] Elio!

356
00:18:53,754 --> 00:18:55,506
Come out, come out,
wherever you are!

357
00:18:55,589 --> 00:18:56,423
[camper] Elio!

358
00:18:56,507 --> 00:18:57,549
[Caleb] Don't you want to
hang out with us?

359
00:18:57,633 --> 00:18:59,009
[camper] I thought you wanted
to meet some aliens.

360
00:18:59,093 --> 00:19:00,677
[Bryce] Come on, it'll be fun.

361
00:19:00,761 --> 00:19:03,180
[grunts, pants]

362
00:19:03,263 --> 00:19:04,932
[Bryce]
He's out here somewhere.

363
00:19:05,432 --> 00:19:08,143
[Caleb] Come on, Space Boy!
We know you're out there.

364
00:19:08,227 --> 00:19:09,353
[punching keys]

365
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:11,563
[static]

366
00:19:11,647 --> 00:19:14,274
[high-frequency humming]

367
00:19:14,358 --> 00:19:16,443
[continuous humming
and beeping]

368
00:19:27,162 --> 00:19:28,664
[gasps]

369
00:19:39,007 --> 00:19:41,135
[phone buzzing]

370
00:19:46,890 --> 00:19:48,475
- [electrical fizzing]
- [Olga startles]

371
00:19:49,109 --> 00:19:49,944
[phone beeps]

372
00:19:54,323 --> 00:19:55,366
[Bryce] Gotcha!

373
00:19:55,449 --> 00:19:57,284
Yeah... You found me.

374
00:19:57,368 --> 00:19:58,369
This is payback.

375
00:19:58,452 --> 00:20:00,746
Eh, it's okay.
You don't need to pay me back.

376
00:20:00,830 --> 00:20:02,998
Wait. What is that?

377
00:20:03,749 --> 00:20:05,501
- Hope you like how it tastes.
- [campers laughing]

378
00:20:05,584 --> 00:20:06,752
There's something back there.

379
00:20:06,836 --> 00:20:08,170
- Look!
- Argh!

380
00:20:08,254 --> 00:20:09,380
[breathing heavily]

381
00:20:09,463 --> 00:20:11,090
You're so dead, Solís.

382
00:20:11,173 --> 00:20:12,508
[Bryce] Hey, hold on.

383
00:20:13,342 --> 00:20:14,301
Wait.

384
00:20:15,052 --> 00:20:16,095
[Elio yells]

385
00:20:19,223 --> 00:20:21,100
[Elio panting]

386
00:20:23,310 --> 00:20:24,144
[gasps]

387
00:20:24,228 --> 00:20:25,604
[panting]

388
00:20:50,588 --> 00:20:52,464
[low humming]

389
00:20:54,174 --> 00:20:55,801
[gasping]

390
00:20:59,930 --> 00:21:03,684
[rhythmic pulsing]

391
00:21:08,022 --> 00:21:09,231
Please.

392
00:21:12,902 --> 00:21:14,945
[elongated gasp]

393
00:21:15,029 --> 00:21:16,405
Yes!

394
00:21:16,488 --> 00:21:17,948
Yes!

395
00:21:19,158 --> 00:21:21,577
It's happening!
It's really happening.

396
00:21:22,953 --> 00:21:24,914
I knew it! I knew it!

397
00:21:24,997 --> 00:21:26,790
Yes!

398
00:21:27,416 --> 00:21:29,293
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

399
00:21:29,376 --> 00:21:32,588
Yes, yes, yes! Yes, yes, yes!

400
00:21:32,671 --> 00:21:34,048
[panting]

401
00:21:34,131 --> 00:21:35,883
[Elio laughing]

402
00:21:37,217 --> 00:21:38,928
Whoa-ho-ho-ho-ho!

403
00:21:40,471 --> 00:21:42,556
Thank you!

404
00:21:47,603 --> 00:21:48,687
[whooping]

405
00:21:48,771 --> 00:21:51,190
Yes! Yeah!

406
00:21:51,273 --> 00:21:52,441
[laughing]

407
00:21:52,524 --> 00:21:53,400
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

408
00:21:53,484 --> 00:21:54,526
Oh!

409
00:21:56,695 --> 00:21:58,072
[Elio exhales]

410
00:21:59,782 --> 00:22:01,450
[chuckling]

411
00:22:02,451 --> 00:22:03,494
Wow.

412
00:22:03,577 --> 00:22:04,828
- [pulsing]
- [Elio gasps]

413
00:22:04,912 --> 00:22:05,746
[panting]

414
00:22:05,829 --> 00:22:06,830
[giggles] Hi.

415
00:22:06,914 --> 00:22:08,499
[electronic burbling]

416
00:22:08,582 --> 00:22:09,583
I knew it!

417
00:22:09,667 --> 00:22:12,836
I knew aliens were looking
for me. You saved my life!

418
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:16,215
I promise I'll pull my weight
on this, uh... spaceship?

419
00:22:16,298 --> 00:22:18,926
Is this a spaceship?
Anyway, where should we start?

420
00:22:19,009 --> 00:22:20,094
Probes? Samples?

421
00:22:20,177 --> 00:22:21,428
I've got plenty.

422
00:22:21,512 --> 00:22:23,931
[musical notes playing]

423
00:22:24,014 --> 00:22:25,099
[gasps]

424
00:22:26,183 --> 00:22:27,184
[Ooooo, distorted]
Testing, testing...

425
00:22:27,267 --> 00:22:28,268
[clear] testing.

426
00:22:28,352 --> 00:22:30,104
Can you understand me now?

427
00:22:30,187 --> 00:22:31,355
Yes. Wow.

428
00:22:31,438 --> 00:22:32,690
It is a pleasure to meet you.

429
00:22:32,773 --> 00:22:36,402
I am Ooooo,
a liquid supercomputer.

430
00:22:36,485 --> 00:22:38,070
Allow me to adjust
your gravity.

431
00:22:38,153 --> 00:22:39,989
- Oh, no, no, no. I'm fine.
- Gravity on.

432
00:22:41,115 --> 00:22:42,116
- [thud]
- [Elio groans]

433
00:22:43,575 --> 00:22:45,119
A welcome glass of glorp,

434
00:22:45,202 --> 00:22:46,829
compliments of
the Communiverse.

435
00:22:46,912 --> 00:22:48,914
Oh! Thank you.

436
00:22:48,998 --> 00:22:50,290
Wait. The what?

437
00:22:50,374 --> 00:22:51,542
Whoa.

438
00:22:54,878 --> 00:22:56,338
[gasping]

439
00:23:06,432 --> 00:23:08,767
[Ooooo] Welcome to
the Communiverse,

440
00:23:08,851 --> 00:23:09,977
a pangalactic organization

441
00:23:10,060 --> 00:23:12,104
of the advanced species
of the cosmos.

442
00:23:12,187 --> 00:23:13,063
Whoa.

443
00:23:13,147 --> 00:23:15,274
The greatest minds
of the universe come here

444
00:23:15,357 --> 00:23:17,026
to share knowledge,
innovation...

445
00:23:17,109 --> 00:23:18,944
[ambassador] And recipes!

446
00:23:19,028 --> 00:23:19,903
Welcome!

447
00:23:19,987 --> 00:23:21,030
- Welcome.
- Lovely.

448
00:23:21,113 --> 00:23:23,032
- [gasps]
- Greetings, Ambassadors!

449
00:23:23,115 --> 00:23:26,243
Absolutely ecstatic
to make your acquaintance.

450
00:23:26,326 --> 00:23:29,913
Oop. You've run dry.
Let me top you off, old brick.

451
00:23:29,997 --> 00:23:31,623
Huh. Thank you.

452
00:23:31,707 --> 00:23:35,127
Hmm, yes.
One cerebellum, four lobes,

453
00:23:35,210 --> 00:23:37,546
and... [gasps] a medulla.

454
00:23:37,629 --> 00:23:39,840
Do you mind if I take
a little peek inside and see?

455
00:23:39,923 --> 00:23:42,885
Questa, don't mind read him,
you've just met him.

456
00:23:42,968 --> 00:23:44,678
[chuckles]
So sorry about that.

457
00:23:44,762 --> 00:23:47,347
I am Questa of Gom.

458
00:23:47,431 --> 00:23:49,767
Helix of Falluvinum. Mwah.

459
00:23:49,850 --> 00:23:51,143
Tegmen of Tegmeg.

460
00:23:51,226 --> 00:23:52,519
And you are?

461
00:23:52,603 --> 00:23:53,687
[gasps]

462
00:23:53,771 --> 00:23:57,858
Elio Solís of, uh... Earth!

463
00:23:57,941 --> 00:24:02,154
A toast to our new candidate,
Elio Solís of Uh-Earth.

464
00:24:02,237 --> 00:24:03,739
[Communiverse members
shouting]

465
00:24:04,364 --> 00:24:05,699
- [ambassador 3] There he is!
- [member] Elio Solís!

466
00:24:05,783 --> 00:24:06,950
[member 2] Look, it's Elio!

467
00:24:07,034 --> 00:24:08,118
[ambassador 4]
It's a new candidate.

468
00:24:08,702 --> 00:24:10,120
Salutations!

469
00:24:10,204 --> 00:24:11,163
I love your eye!

470
00:24:11,246 --> 00:24:12,081
[chuckling]

471
00:24:12,164 --> 00:24:13,749
We search the universe

472
00:24:13,832 --> 00:24:16,502
for like-minded souls
and new species,

473
00:24:16,585 --> 00:24:18,796
and we think you're
an excellent candidate

474
00:24:18,879 --> 00:24:20,881
for Communiverse membership.

475
00:24:21,715 --> 00:24:23,383
You mean I could stay here?

476
00:24:23,467 --> 00:24:26,303
If all the members agree,
then, yes.

477
00:24:26,386 --> 00:24:31,183
You'll be one of us and be the
proud bearer of one of these.

478
00:24:31,850 --> 00:24:34,561
Now come,
everyone's eager to meet you.

479
00:24:41,276 --> 00:24:42,361
[Questa] Each of us brings

480
00:24:42,444 --> 00:24:45,155
our specialized knowledge
and interest to share.

481
00:24:45,239 --> 00:24:46,323
Greetings, Naos!

482
00:24:46,406 --> 00:24:47,741
[Naos] Hello. Salutations.

483
00:24:47,825 --> 00:24:50,619
Naos, here, created
the Communidiscs we all use

484
00:24:50,702 --> 00:24:52,329
with controls for gravity...

485
00:24:52,996 --> 00:24:54,540
[Elio yells]

486
00:24:55,045 --> 00:24:56,797
- [Questa] ...temperature...
- [shivering]

487
00:24:56,880 --> 00:24:58,799
...and all known languages.

488
00:24:58,882 --> 00:25:01,301
[gasps] You know Elioese?

489
00:25:01,385 --> 00:25:02,678
[in Elioese]

490
00:25:06,807 --> 00:25:07,808
[both laughing]

491
00:25:07,891 --> 00:25:08,725
<i>-Gloodle.
- Gloodle.</i>

492
00:25:08,809 --> 00:25:09,810
[ambassadors] <i>Gloodle!</i>

493
00:25:10,235 --> 00:25:13,488
This is my most recent design.
Try it.

494
00:25:13,572 --> 00:25:17,117
Hello. I am
the Universal Users Manual.

495
00:25:17,201 --> 00:25:19,703
I contain the secrets
of the universe.

496
00:25:19,786 --> 00:25:21,747
What is the meaning of life?

497
00:25:21,830 --> 00:25:24,791
What lies beyond a black hole?
Is there a purpose to...

498
00:25:24,875 --> 00:25:25,834
[Elio]
Who would win in a fight?

499
00:25:25,918 --> 00:25:28,378
One gorilla with
a baseball bat or ten chimps?

500
00:25:28,462 --> 00:25:31,423
None who fight
are true winners.

501
00:25:32,049 --> 00:25:32,883
Huh?

502
00:25:32,966 --> 00:25:34,468
[UUM sighs]

503
00:25:34,551 --> 00:25:35,552
The gorilla.

504
00:25:35,636 --> 00:25:37,471
Wow.

505
00:25:38,138 --> 00:25:40,766
These little critters
are mimollusks.

506
00:25:40,849 --> 00:25:44,269
They use nanotechnology to
construct anything you desire.

507
00:25:44,353 --> 00:25:45,896
[Elio laughing]

508
00:25:49,233 --> 00:25:50,067
[gasps]

509
00:25:50,150 --> 00:25:51,568
Are you kidding me?

510
00:25:51,652 --> 00:25:53,153
[Questa] How dashing!

511
00:25:55,447 --> 00:25:57,908
[gasps] This is
the most beautiful place

512
00:25:57,991 --> 00:25:59,451
I've ever seen.

513
00:25:59,534 --> 00:26:01,036
This is the bathroom.

514
00:26:01,119 --> 00:26:02,037
[flushing]

515
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:03,872
[all] Whee!

516
00:26:04,623 --> 00:26:05,582
[all laughing]

517
00:26:05,666 --> 00:26:07,542
- [Questa] Gets me every time.
- Bracing.

518
00:26:08,543 --> 00:26:11,004
It's like I was always
meant to be here.

519
00:26:11,588 --> 00:26:13,257
I knew you were
looking for me.

520
00:26:13,340 --> 00:26:15,217
Of course we were
looking for you.

521
00:26:15,300 --> 00:26:16,301
Ever since we picked up

522
00:26:16,385 --> 00:26:18,971
this charming little
spacecraft you sent us.

523
00:26:21,932 --> 00:26:23,475
[gasps] <i>Voyager?</i>

524
00:26:23,558 --> 00:26:25,435
[Helix] We found it
in an asteroid field.

525
00:26:25,519 --> 00:26:27,312
[Tegmen] Nice craftsmanship.

526
00:26:27,396 --> 00:26:29,398
Um... thanks?

527
00:26:34,236 --> 00:26:36,071
[Helix] Curious about
the species who made it,

528
00:26:36,154 --> 00:26:37,698
we sent an invitation

529
00:26:37,781 --> 00:26:41,243
and were delighted to receive
your planet's official reply.

530
00:26:41,910 --> 00:26:44,329
[distorted] <i>This is Elio Solis
of the planet Earth</i>

531
00:26:44,413 --> 00:26:46,623
<i>and I'm super excited
to join you.</i>

532
00:26:46,707 --> 00:26:49,543
<i>I'm creative, hard-working,
shredded!</i>

533
00:26:49,626 --> 00:26:50,794
[static, interference]

534
00:26:50,877 --> 00:26:52,004
<i>So, please come and get me.
I'll be waiting.</i>

535
00:26:52,087 --> 00:26:53,380
<i>Okay, bye. Love you.</i>

536
00:26:53,463 --> 00:26:55,549
- [Tegmen] Very touching.
- We are delighted

537
00:26:55,632 --> 00:26:57,759
to finally make
your acquaintance,

538
00:26:57,843 --> 00:27:00,137
Leader of Uh-Earth.

539
00:27:01,972 --> 00:27:02,973
Ooh.

540
00:27:03,056 --> 00:27:03,890
Uh...

541
00:27:03,974 --> 00:27:05,559
[Tegmen]
Why is your face melting?

542
00:27:05,642 --> 00:27:06,518
Um...

543
00:27:06,601 --> 00:27:07,728
- Well...
- Ambassadors,

544
00:27:07,811 --> 00:27:09,730
an urgent matter
requires your attention.

545
00:27:09,813 --> 00:27:11,440
It involves
the other candidate.

546
00:27:11,523 --> 00:27:12,899
- Oh, him.
- [Questa] Oh, dear.

547
00:27:12,983 --> 00:27:14,318
[Helix] We should hurry.
Quickly now!

548
00:27:14,401 --> 00:27:15,402
[Questa] Excuse us.

549
00:27:17,988 --> 00:27:19,323
Please join us.

550
00:27:24,578 --> 00:27:26,621
Your technology and my weapons

551
00:27:26,705 --> 00:27:28,874
would be
an unstoppable alliance.

552
00:27:29,624 --> 00:27:31,626
Now, admit me
to your Communiverse!

553
00:27:31,710 --> 00:27:33,211
[ambassadors muttering]

554
00:27:34,379 --> 00:27:36,340
Unfortunately,
Candidate Grigon,

555
00:27:36,423 --> 00:27:38,633
it is our assessment
that you are

556
00:27:38,717 --> 00:27:39,801
not a fit.

557
00:27:39,885 --> 00:27:41,970
I, Lord Grigon,

558
00:27:42,054 --> 00:27:46,475
Blood Emperor of Hylurg,
not a fit?

559
00:27:47,225 --> 00:27:50,937
Well, we believe in tolerance
and open-mindedness...

560
00:27:51,438 --> 00:27:53,357
I am tolerant!

561
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,984
So sorry, it's not you,

562
00:27:56,068 --> 00:27:57,652
it's us.

563
00:27:59,071 --> 00:28:00,572
[Tegmen] I thought we said
it was him.

564
00:28:00,655 --> 00:28:01,490
[Helix] Shh!

565
00:28:01,573 --> 00:28:04,201
If I cannot join
the Communiverse,

566
00:28:04,284 --> 00:28:07,204
then I shall take it by force!

567
00:28:07,287 --> 00:28:09,331
Prepare to be conquered!

568
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:12,834
[ambassadors screaming]

569
00:28:12,918 --> 00:28:14,044
[ambassador 4] What a brute!

570
00:28:14,127 --> 00:28:15,379
Why did he make a new hole?

571
00:28:15,462 --> 00:28:17,005
[Naos] I suggest
we run and hide.

572
00:28:17,089 --> 00:28:18,673
Yes, let's go to the edge
of the cosmos

573
00:28:18,757 --> 00:28:20,008
and turn off all the lights.

574
00:28:20,092 --> 00:28:22,803
Uh, that includes me, right?

575
00:28:22,886 --> 00:28:25,013
Oh, so sorry, candidate Solís,

576
00:28:25,097 --> 00:28:27,766
we couldn't possibly accept
new members

577
00:28:27,849 --> 00:28:29,434
under the current situation.

578
00:28:29,518 --> 00:28:31,478
Applications
are closed indefinitely.

579
00:28:31,561 --> 00:28:33,230
- But I just got here!
- [Helix] Such a shame.

580
00:28:33,313 --> 00:28:35,941
Let's check back
in a few thousand years?

581
00:28:36,024 --> 00:28:37,692
Perhaps one of us
could talk to Lord Grigon.

582
00:28:37,776 --> 00:28:38,777
- You do it!
- Not me.

583
00:28:38,860 --> 00:28:40,654
- I am shy.
- I'm busy.

584
00:28:40,737 --> 00:28:42,489
- I have allergies.
- [Naos] My battery is low.

585
00:28:42,572 --> 00:28:45,117
Don't worry. I'll return you
to your life on Uh-Earth

586
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:47,411
just as it was...
[echoing] was, was, was...

587
00:28:47,953 --> 00:28:49,329
<i>Just as it was...</i>

588
00:28:50,122 --> 00:28:52,541
No, no!

589
00:28:53,875 --> 00:28:54,876
I'll do it.

590
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,294
[panting]

591
00:28:57,379 --> 00:28:58,713
I'm the leader of Earth.

592
00:28:59,256 --> 00:29:01,174
I'm the perfect guy
for the job.

593
00:29:01,883 --> 00:29:02,968
[Helix] What did it say?

594
00:29:03,051 --> 00:29:04,428
- [ambassador 4] How curious.
- [Tegmen] I do not understand.

595
00:29:04,511 --> 00:29:05,971
You would talk to Lord Grigon?

596
00:29:06,054 --> 00:29:06,930
[Naos] But what would you say?

597
00:29:07,013 --> 00:29:09,391
Are you an expert
on conflict negotiation?

598
00:29:09,474 --> 00:29:10,725
[sputters] You kidding?

599
00:29:10,809 --> 00:29:13,437
My life is nothing
but conflict

600
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:16,273
and I've got the battle scars
to prove it.

601
00:29:18,191 --> 00:29:20,277
It would be a welcome change

602
00:29:20,360 --> 00:29:23,697
not to flee every bully
who covets our treasures.

603
00:29:24,412 --> 00:29:26,498
[in alien language]

604
00:29:26,581 --> 00:29:27,791
Yes. What's in it for you?

605
00:29:27,874 --> 00:29:30,752
Why would you agree
to such a dangerous mission?

606
00:29:31,419 --> 00:29:32,420
Because...

607
00:29:32,962 --> 00:29:33,963
you need me.

608
00:29:34,798 --> 00:29:38,593
And at my age,
it's really about giving back.

609
00:29:38,930 --> 00:29:41,098
If you can make Grigon
go away,

610
00:29:41,182 --> 00:29:43,225
we'd make you a member
on the spot.

611
00:29:43,309 --> 00:29:44,226
[giggles]

612
00:29:44,310 --> 00:29:47,688
Then I, the leader of Earth,
am ready to serve.

613
00:29:47,772 --> 00:29:48,981
- [Tegmen] Good. Very good.
- How impressive!

614
00:29:49,065 --> 00:29:51,025
- [ambassador 2] What courage!
- [Naos] Wonderful!

615
00:29:51,108 --> 00:29:54,236
Candidate Solís,
you continue to surprise.

616
00:29:54,320 --> 00:29:57,657
When Grigon returns,
we shall be ready for him.

617
00:29:57,740 --> 00:30:00,284
Until then,
as you say on Uh-Earth.

618
00:30:00,368 --> 00:30:02,411
Okay, bye. I love you.

619
00:30:02,495 --> 00:30:04,830
[ambassadors, together]
Okay. Bye. I love you.

620
00:30:04,914 --> 00:30:06,582
Don't worry. I got this.

621
00:30:06,666 --> 00:30:08,376
You're in great hands.

622
00:30:09,710 --> 00:30:11,170
[restrained shrieking]

623
00:30:11,671 --> 00:30:13,089
Just one last
order of business.

624
00:30:13,172 --> 00:30:14,340
Oh, yeah, of course.

625
00:30:16,008 --> 00:30:17,718
While you negotiate
with the warlord,

626
00:30:17,802 --> 00:30:19,095
you'll need
a temporary replacement.

627
00:30:19,178 --> 00:30:20,012
[Elio] Whoa.

628
00:30:20,096 --> 00:30:22,056
[Ooooo] Can I trouble you
for a DNA sample?

629
00:30:22,139 --> 00:30:23,641
Sure. Where do you want it...
Argh!

630
00:30:24,850 --> 00:30:26,602
Yeow! [groans]

631
00:30:32,149 --> 00:30:34,485
Wow. My first probe.

632
00:30:34,568 --> 00:30:35,945
[Elio laughing]

633
00:30:36,028 --> 00:30:37,738
World leaders,
such as yourself,

634
00:30:37,822 --> 00:30:39,031
can't just disappear.

635
00:30:39,115 --> 00:30:41,367
Your planet would descend
into chaos.

636
00:30:41,450 --> 00:30:42,410
[ticking]

637
00:30:42,493 --> 00:30:44,745
That's what cloning clay
is for.

638
00:30:46,914 --> 00:30:47,748
[bell dings]

639
00:30:50,960 --> 00:30:51,836
Whoa.

640
00:30:51,919 --> 00:30:53,921
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

641
00:31:05,307 --> 00:31:06,517
[both] Whoa.

642
00:31:08,853 --> 00:31:09,812
Is this...?

643
00:31:09,895 --> 00:31:11,397
Are you...?

644
00:31:11,480 --> 00:31:12,314
[both] Me?

645
00:31:12,398 --> 00:31:13,232
[both laugh]

646
00:31:13,315 --> 00:31:14,233
Rock...

647
00:31:14,316 --> 00:31:15,234
Paper...

648
00:31:15,317 --> 00:31:16,527
[both] Black hole! Oh!

649
00:31:17,403 --> 00:31:19,363
- Space is the best!
- Space is amazing!

650
00:31:23,576 --> 00:31:24,702
In you go.

651
00:31:24,785 --> 00:31:25,870
Sorry.

652
00:31:25,953 --> 00:31:27,079
It's a living.

653
00:31:27,163 --> 00:31:28,789
So, what is my motivation?

654
00:31:28,873 --> 00:31:29,957
What do you mean?

655
00:31:30,041 --> 00:31:31,625
Should I change anything

656
00:31:31,709 --> 00:31:33,294
or just stick with
the low self-esteem

657
00:31:33,377 --> 00:31:34,336
and desperation to belong?

658
00:31:34,420 --> 00:31:37,590
What?
I'm normal, just be normal.

659
00:31:37,673 --> 00:31:39,008
No weird stuff, okay?

660
00:31:39,091 --> 00:31:40,718
- Okay.
- Okay.

661
00:31:47,808 --> 00:31:48,809
Have fun.

662
00:31:48,893 --> 00:31:49,727
- [blow lands]
- [Other Elio grunts]

663
00:31:49,810 --> 00:31:53,064
Intriguing Uh-Earth custom.
The warlord awaits.

664
00:31:53,147 --> 00:31:55,524
Oh, uh, there was, uh,
just a few things

665
00:31:55,608 --> 00:31:56,942
I wanted to brush up on.

666
00:31:57,026 --> 00:31:58,652
Where was that thing that knew
everything about everything?

667
00:31:58,736 --> 00:31:59,737
You mean this?

668
00:31:59,820 --> 00:32:02,907
Hello. I am
the Universal Users Manual.

669
00:32:02,990 --> 00:32:05,868
Would you like to learn the
meaning of life now? It's a...

670
00:32:05,951 --> 00:32:06,952
No. I need everything
you've got

671
00:32:07,036 --> 00:32:08,621
on how to negotiate
with the warmonger.

672
00:32:08,704 --> 00:32:10,164
[sighs]

673
00:32:10,247 --> 00:32:11,707
Certainly.

674
00:32:11,791 --> 00:32:13,709
I have chapters on leading
with empathy.

675
00:32:13,793 --> 00:32:14,627
Nope.

676
00:32:14,710 --> 00:32:16,003
- [UUM]Fostering connection?
- Nope.

677
00:32:16,087 --> 00:32:17,630
[UUM] Making the killer deal?

678
00:32:17,713 --> 00:32:19,423
Yes, that one.
Do you have a pen?

679
00:32:19,507 --> 00:32:22,343
In the increasingly likely
event that you will die,

680
00:32:22,426 --> 00:32:25,387
would you like to notify
your next of kin on Uh-Earth?

681
00:32:25,471 --> 00:32:26,597
No, that's okay.

682
00:32:26,680 --> 00:32:28,933
[UUM] Start from
a position of power.

683
00:32:29,016 --> 00:32:32,561
The most important thing
is to stay calm.

684
00:32:32,812 --> 00:32:34,522
Don't you tell me
to stay calm!

685
00:32:34,605 --> 00:32:36,690
What is this, huh?
A camp or a fight club?

686
00:32:36,774 --> 00:32:38,651
He's an innocent little boy,

687
00:32:38,734 --> 00:32:41,695
and if this is what you call
"building character,"

688
00:32:41,779 --> 00:32:44,240
then I'll take it up
with your-- with your boss,

689
00:32:44,323 --> 00:32:45,825
- or her-- her boss.
- [Other Elio humming]

690
00:32:45,908 --> 00:32:47,076
Everyone's boss!

691
00:32:47,159 --> 00:32:48,452
Unacceptable!

692
00:32:52,545 --> 00:32:54,005
I never should have
left you here.

693
00:32:54,088 --> 00:32:56,424
Yeah, they chased me
because I'm weak and small,

694
00:32:56,507 --> 00:32:58,009
but there was pizza
for dinner.

695
00:32:58,092 --> 00:32:59,677
So, overall,
a pretty good night.

696
00:32:59,760 --> 00:33:01,429
How's the eye? Swollen?

697
00:33:01,512 --> 00:33:02,638
- Did they hurt it?
- It's fine.

698
00:33:02,722 --> 00:33:04,557
I'm-I'm... I'm so sorry
I didn't check in.

699
00:33:04,640 --> 00:33:06,267
Something weird was happening.

700
00:33:07,360 --> 00:33:08,361
That's okay.

701
00:33:08,445 --> 00:33:10,530
I was tracking this
crazy signal from space...

702
00:33:10,614 --> 00:33:12,282
Are we going home?
What's for dinner?

703
00:33:12,365 --> 00:33:14,242
- [static on radio]
- Um...

704
00:33:14,326 --> 00:33:15,577
Mac and cheese.

705
00:33:15,660 --> 00:33:17,120
I just thought
you'd be interested

706
00:33:17,203 --> 00:33:20,540
because if aliens
were calling from space...

707
00:33:20,624 --> 00:33:21,958
[radio announcer]
<i>Early morning fog and clouds</i>

708
00:33:22,042 --> 00:33:23,251
<i>along the coast...</i>

709
00:33:23,335 --> 00:33:24,252
Elio?

710
00:33:24,336 --> 00:33:26,921
Are we doing regular
or white cheddar? I'm starved.

711
00:33:27,005 --> 00:33:28,965
So, you-you-you don't want
to talk about aliens?

712
00:33:29,049 --> 00:33:31,718
Not really. I thought it'd be
better if I just dropped it.

713
00:33:31,801 --> 00:33:33,511
- [radio stations changing]
- Really?

714
00:33:34,554 --> 00:33:36,640
That's... amazing.

715
00:33:37,599 --> 00:33:38,558
Good for you.

716
00:33:38,642 --> 00:33:39,768
Ooh!

717
00:33:39,851 --> 00:33:41,061
[♪ Juan Luis Guerra
"Como Abeja Al Panal" playing]

718
00:33:41,144 --> 00:33:42,812
Oh. I love this song.

719
00:33:42,896 --> 00:33:44,898
[song continues playing]

720
00:33:52,155 --> 00:33:53,365
[gasps]

721
00:33:53,448 --> 00:33:54,449
Do you see him?

722
00:33:55,742 --> 00:33:57,535
[Helix]
Yes, and he's brought his...

723
00:33:58,370 --> 00:33:59,996
compatriots. Heh.

724
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:01,081
Jolly good.

725
00:34:01,164 --> 00:34:04,584
Okay. Be confident. Speak
from a position of power.

726
00:34:04,668 --> 00:34:05,877
[ambassador 3] He's here!

727
00:34:05,960 --> 00:34:07,879
He's here. There he is.

728
00:34:07,962 --> 00:34:09,339
The man of the hour.

729
00:34:09,422 --> 00:34:10,715
Ah. Sorry I'm late.

730
00:34:10,799 --> 00:34:13,426
So, is Lord Grigon
coming here?

731
00:34:13,510 --> 00:34:16,012
Oh, no.
You will be going out there.

732
00:34:16,096 --> 00:34:17,472
[yelps, grunts]

733
00:34:17,555 --> 00:34:19,015
Okay, bye. Love you.

734
00:34:21,525 --> 00:34:22,776
[Elio] What is this?

735
00:34:23,318 --> 00:34:24,862
Red? Green?

736
00:34:24,945 --> 00:34:26,488
[ship]
<i>Welcome, Captain Solís.</i>

737
00:34:26,572 --> 00:34:28,282
<i>You have selected
a map of our coordinates.</i>

738
00:34:28,365 --> 00:34:29,700
<i>Cabin pressure.
Shield function.</i>

739
00:34:29,783 --> 00:34:31,577
<i>A nutritious shake.
A breath mint.</i>

740
00:34:31,660 --> 00:34:32,786
<i>A bladder evacuation module.</i>

741
00:34:32,870 --> 00:34:34,663
Ah, he found the mint.

742
00:34:36,290 --> 00:34:37,791
<i>You have set our destination
to your home planet.</i>

743
00:34:38,755 --> 00:34:40,298
[Elio's voice] <i>Uh-Earth.</i>

744
00:34:40,382 --> 00:34:41,925
[ship] <i>Confirm or cancel?</i>

745
00:34:43,176 --> 00:34:44,427
Uh...

746
00:34:46,012 --> 00:34:47,347
Good luck.

747
00:34:49,099 --> 00:34:50,100
[exhales]

748
00:34:51,059 --> 00:34:52,060
Cancel.

749
00:34:56,439 --> 00:34:57,899
[screaming]

750
00:34:58,650 --> 00:35:00,443
Uh, okay, okay.

751
00:35:05,574 --> 00:35:06,533
[Questa] A little to the left.

752
00:35:06,616 --> 00:35:08,743
Get your nubs at ten and two.

753
00:35:11,538 --> 00:35:13,331
[Elio] Whoa!

754
00:35:13,415 --> 00:35:15,542
What a heroic figure he cuts.

755
00:35:15,625 --> 00:35:18,253
[shrieking, crying]

756
00:35:19,671 --> 00:35:21,464
[breathing heavily]

757
00:35:28,221 --> 00:35:29,723
[pulsing]

758
00:35:33,435 --> 00:35:34,936
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

759
00:35:45,322 --> 00:35:48,867
Hi. Take me to your leader?

760
00:35:55,207 --> 00:35:58,293
Okay, look him in the eye.
Stand your ground.

761
00:35:58,877 --> 00:36:00,587
You're the alpha,
you're the killer.

762
00:36:00,670 --> 00:36:01,713
You're... [yelps]

763
00:36:08,136 --> 00:36:10,680
This is who
the Communiverse sends?

764
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:16,436
You are more puny
than I expected.

765
00:36:16,519 --> 00:36:18,480
I could say the same
about you.

766
00:36:19,522 --> 00:36:21,274
- What?
- Uh...

767
00:36:21,358 --> 00:36:23,944
What do you need to leave
the Communiverse alone?

768
00:36:24,027 --> 00:36:28,073
Hylurgians prefer to negotiate
with screams in the air.

769
00:36:30,492 --> 00:36:31,576
Pull!

770
00:36:32,535 --> 00:36:33,370
[creature exclaims]

771
00:36:34,537 --> 00:36:35,622
[gasping]

772
00:36:36,206 --> 00:36:37,207
[yelps]

773
00:36:37,290 --> 00:36:38,333
[groans]

774
00:36:38,416 --> 00:36:39,417
[squeaks]

775
00:36:39,501 --> 00:36:40,669
[gulps]

776
00:36:41,378 --> 00:36:43,505
Recoil's a little heavy.

777
00:36:45,423 --> 00:36:46,424
Your turn.

778
00:36:48,343 --> 00:36:51,972
Darn! I, uh,
left my arm cannon at home.

779
00:36:52,055 --> 00:36:53,139
Why-Why don't we...

780
00:36:53,223 --> 00:36:54,266
[yelps]

781
00:36:55,433 --> 00:36:56,977
Use one of mine.

782
00:36:57,060 --> 00:36:58,561
So nice of you.

783
00:36:58,645 --> 00:37:00,105
Uh...

784
00:37:00,605 --> 00:37:01,606
[grunts]

785
00:37:02,274 --> 00:37:04,401
I-I mean, we're both leaders
and, uh...

786
00:37:04,484 --> 00:37:05,819
Pull!

787
00:37:06,403 --> 00:37:07,570
[exclaims]

788
00:37:07,654 --> 00:37:10,782
Surely we could find something
to everyone's mutual...

789
00:37:12,033 --> 00:37:13,034
[yelps]

790
00:37:13,118 --> 00:37:14,202
...benefit.

791
00:37:14,286 --> 00:37:15,996
Ah, trick shot.

792
00:37:16,079 --> 00:37:18,999
Perhaps we are able
to communicate...

793
00:37:19,082 --> 00:37:19,916
Pull!

794
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:22,585
But those
Communiverse weaklings

795
00:37:22,669 --> 00:37:25,338
look at me like
some kind of monster.

796
00:37:25,422 --> 00:37:27,007
How dare they reject me!

797
00:37:27,090 --> 00:37:27,924
[squeaking]

798
00:37:28,008 --> 00:37:29,301
[all yelp]

799
00:37:31,271 --> 00:37:32,689
Well, if they don't
want you...

800
00:37:33,231 --> 00:37:35,317
why not find
someone who does?

801
00:37:35,900 --> 00:37:36,985
Come again?

802
00:37:37,068 --> 00:37:38,695
There's got to be
a place out there

803
00:37:38,778 --> 00:37:42,616
that would love to have
a strong guy like you.

804
00:37:42,699 --> 00:37:44,117
But is the Communiverse not

805
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:46,369
where the greatest leaders
gather?

806
00:37:47,039 --> 00:37:48,416
Am I not great?

807
00:37:48,499 --> 00:37:49,583
T-Totally.

808
00:37:49,667 --> 00:37:51,460
But why waste your life

809
00:37:51,544 --> 00:37:53,671
trying to connect with people
who don't get you?

810
00:37:54,255 --> 00:37:55,715
It's time to move on.

811
00:37:55,798 --> 00:37:57,883
Right, Gri-guy?

812
00:37:58,509 --> 00:37:59,510
Gri-guy?

813
00:38:00,010 --> 00:38:01,637
[chuckles] Hmm, yes.

814
00:38:01,721 --> 00:38:03,431
What, Workko? What is it?

815
00:38:03,514 --> 00:38:05,891
Your Wrath, the princeling
wants to see you.

816
00:38:05,975 --> 00:38:09,395
For the hate of...
Tell him I am busy!

817
00:38:09,478 --> 00:38:12,732
So, as we were saying,
forget the Communiverse. <i>..</i>

818
00:38:12,815 --> 00:38:14,191
You are a father, right?

819
00:38:14,775 --> 00:38:16,527
Oh. Yeah. [chuckles]

820
00:38:16,610 --> 00:38:18,195
It is so difficult!

821
00:38:18,279 --> 00:38:22,032
He has no concept
of the importance of my work.

822
00:38:22,116 --> 00:38:23,117
I get it.

823
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:26,078
If he's too hard to handle,
then just ship him <i>off.</i>

824
00:38:26,162 --> 00:38:27,788
That's what I did with mine.
So...

825
00:38:28,124 --> 00:38:30,293
[Grigon] "Too hard to handle"?

826
00:38:34,047 --> 00:38:35,089
I-I mean...

827
00:38:35,173 --> 00:38:37,509
Oh, you think I cannot
handle my own son?

828
00:38:37,592 --> 00:38:39,219
No, no, no.
I-I don't think that...

829
00:38:39,302 --> 00:38:41,805
No! Really. Tell me what
I am doing wrong!

830
00:38:41,888 --> 00:38:44,557
[yelps] It's okay.
I'm a bad parent too.

831
00:38:44,641 --> 00:38:45,975
What?

832
00:38:46,059 --> 00:38:47,310
None of us know
what we're doing.

833
00:38:47,393 --> 00:38:49,229
We-We didn't even
want this, right?

834
00:38:49,733 --> 00:38:51,985
Let me remind you
who you are dealing with!

835
00:38:52,069 --> 00:38:56,114
I am Grigon,
Blood Emperor of Hylurg,

836
00:38:56,198 --> 00:39:00,911
scourge of the Crab Nebula
and a great father!

837
00:39:00,994 --> 00:39:02,204
Pull!

838
00:39:04,956 --> 00:39:06,249
[all scream]

839
00:39:06,833 --> 00:39:09,378
[stammering] Right, why don't
we take a little breather...

840
00:39:09,461 --> 00:39:11,713
The negotiation is over.

841
00:39:11,797 --> 00:39:12,631
Gronk!

842
00:39:12,714 --> 00:39:15,008
Show the prisoner
to his quarters!

843
00:39:15,092 --> 00:39:16,385
Prisoner? What?

844
00:39:16,468 --> 00:39:18,261
You will watch from a cell

845
00:39:18,345 --> 00:39:21,306
as I destroy
your beloved Communiverse!

846
00:39:21,390 --> 00:39:22,808
No, no, wait!

847
00:39:26,103 --> 00:39:27,938
He's really
turned over a new leaf.

848
00:39:28,897 --> 00:39:31,316
- Hey, Elio.
- Hey, Jim. How's your back?

849
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:33,193
- Oh, you know...
- I hear ya.

850
00:39:33,276 --> 00:39:35,487
Oh, camp must've
really helped.

851
00:39:35,570 --> 00:39:36,947
[chuckles] I guess it did.

852
00:39:37,030 --> 00:39:39,908
But he was only there
for one day.

853
00:39:39,991 --> 00:39:42,411
Oh, I overheard
the colonel raving about you.

854
00:39:42,494 --> 00:39:44,246
[gasps] Really? She was?

855
00:39:44,329 --> 00:39:45,330
Yeah.

856
00:39:45,414 --> 00:39:46,832
You've been working
really hard.

857
00:39:46,915 --> 00:39:48,750
Oh, that's so good to hear.

858
00:39:48,834 --> 00:39:51,086
I thought I'd never
get off her bad side.

859
00:39:51,169 --> 00:39:52,045
Oopsie.

860
00:39:52,129 --> 00:39:53,880
Everyone's super impressed.

861
00:39:53,964 --> 00:39:55,340
[both chuckle]

862
00:39:58,552 --> 00:40:00,762
Wait, please.
You made a mistake.

863
00:40:00,846 --> 00:40:02,597
I'm the leader of Earth!

864
00:40:03,348 --> 00:40:04,641
[groans]

865
00:40:08,186 --> 00:40:09,688
[♪ Melancholic music playing]

866
00:40:13,734 --> 00:40:14,860
[coughs]

867
00:40:25,245 --> 00:40:26,246
[sighs]

868
00:40:27,205 --> 00:40:28,540
[bones crunch]

869
00:40:28,623 --> 00:40:29,583
[groans]

870
00:40:30,751 --> 00:40:31,752
[grunts]

871
00:40:33,920 --> 00:40:35,088
[gasps]

872
00:40:37,090 --> 00:40:40,385
Uh, gravity, um... off.

873
00:40:41,052 --> 00:40:42,137
Whoa.

874
00:40:43,680 --> 00:40:45,682
[grunting]

875
00:40:51,021 --> 00:40:53,064
Okay, th-that's enough!
Gravity back!

876
00:40:53,148 --> 00:40:55,400
[grunting]

877
00:40:56,109 --> 00:40:58,403
Okay. I'll just get back
to Grigon.

878
00:40:58,487 --> 00:40:59,613
Uh, what haven't I tried?

879
00:41:00,706 --> 00:41:03,959
"Bargaining chip"?
Like, something valuable?

880
00:41:04,043 --> 00:41:05,336
[scoffs]
Where am I going to find...

881
00:41:05,419 --> 00:41:06,420
[screams]

882
00:41:06,504 --> 00:41:08,047
[grunting, screaming]

883
00:41:08,923 --> 00:41:10,549
[panting]

884
00:41:13,719 --> 00:41:15,346
[creature chittering]

885
00:41:15,429 --> 00:41:16,430
[whimpers]

886
00:41:17,274 --> 00:41:19,068
[straining]

887
00:41:19,151 --> 00:41:19,985
[gasps]

888
00:41:20,069 --> 00:41:22,071
[chittering]

889
00:41:22,154 --> 00:41:23,280
[Elio whimpers]

890
00:41:26,784 --> 00:41:28,285
[growling]

891
00:41:28,911 --> 00:41:30,204
H-Hi, there.

892
00:41:30,287 --> 00:41:32,665
[screeching]

893
00:41:32,748 --> 00:41:33,999
[exclaims]

894
00:41:38,212 --> 00:41:40,756
I'm too young to die.
I'm too young to die.

895
00:41:40,839 --> 00:41:42,591
I'm too young to die.

896
00:41:45,886 --> 00:41:47,721
[disc whirs, beeps]

897
00:41:47,805 --> 00:41:50,432
[distorted] What's happening?
[clear] What's happening?

898
00:41:50,516 --> 00:41:53,185
Whoa. Translator disc, cool.

899
00:41:53,269 --> 00:41:54,687
- Are you going to eat me?
- What?

900
00:41:54,770 --> 00:41:58,315
Ew. I was just swaddling you
because you seemed scared.

901
00:41:58,399 --> 00:42:00,484
That's what my mom does
when I get scared.

902
00:42:00,568 --> 00:42:03,070
I'm rarely unswaddled.

903
00:42:03,153 --> 00:42:04,655
You're just a little kid.

904
00:42:05,281 --> 00:42:07,950
So? Don't have
to be rude about it.

905
00:42:09,326 --> 00:42:11,579
Oh. No, no, no.
Hey, come back!

906
00:42:11,662 --> 00:42:12,997
I wasn't making fun of you!

907
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:13,914
[strains]

908
00:42:13,998 --> 00:42:16,292
Uh, my name's Elio.

909
00:42:16,375 --> 00:42:18,043
W-What's your name?

910
00:42:18,127 --> 00:42:20,212
You really want
to know my name?

911
00:42:20,296 --> 00:42:23,299
Well, I really want
to get down.

912
00:42:23,382 --> 00:42:26,552
I'm Glordon! No one's ever
asked me my name before.

913
00:42:26,635 --> 00:42:27,469
[Elio screams]

914
00:42:27,553 --> 00:42:29,221
I mean, I ask a lot
of questions all the time.

915
00:42:29,305 --> 00:42:31,682
No one ever asks me about
questions about me, though.

916
00:42:31,765 --> 00:42:33,309
Like what
my favorite color is.

917
00:42:33,392 --> 00:42:35,436
It's purple, if you're asking.
Are you asking?

918
00:42:35,519 --> 00:42:36,353
[yelps]

919
00:42:36,937 --> 00:42:38,939
[shrieks]

920
00:42:42,192 --> 00:42:44,778
What's wrong with you?
That's just my carapace.

921
00:42:44,862 --> 00:42:46,780
- W-What?
- I'll show you.

922
00:42:54,788 --> 00:42:56,332
Ta-da!

923
00:42:56,415 --> 00:42:57,416
Whoa.

924
00:42:58,042 --> 00:43:00,628
Every Hylurgian gets one
when they come of age.

925
00:43:00,711 --> 00:43:03,088
It's got weapons
and bombs and stuff.

926
00:43:03,172 --> 00:43:04,715
Ooh, and a cup holder!

927
00:43:04,798 --> 00:43:06,342
It's bespoke.

928
00:43:06,425 --> 00:43:09,386
So, if Hylurgians
took off their armor,

929
00:43:09,470 --> 00:43:10,471
they'd look like you?

930
00:43:10,554 --> 00:43:12,681
Yeah, but nobody
would ever do that.

931
00:43:12,765 --> 00:43:14,975
To expose
your soft, warm flesh

932
00:43:15,059 --> 00:43:17,061
would dishonor you
and your whole family

933
00:43:17,144 --> 00:43:18,562
for all eternity.

934
00:43:18,646 --> 00:43:19,980
I can't wait to get installed.

935
00:43:20,564 --> 00:43:22,024
I'm going to look so hot.

936
00:43:22,107 --> 00:43:22,941
[alarm blaring]

937
00:43:23,025 --> 00:43:24,860
[voice on PA]
<i>Alert! A prisoner has escaped.</i>

938
00:43:24,943 --> 00:43:26,487
- Oh, no.
- Are they talking about you?

939
00:43:26,570 --> 00:43:28,906
Uh, it's a complicated
political situation.

940
00:43:28,989 --> 00:43:30,157
You-You wouldn't understand.

941
00:43:30,240 --> 00:43:31,367
Are you
a treacherous dissident?

942
00:43:31,450 --> 00:43:32,868
[guard 1] Where is he?
Check every chamber!

943
00:43:32,951 --> 00:43:33,786
[Glordon] Are you an assassin?

944
00:43:33,869 --> 00:43:35,037
[guard 1]
You two with me. Move!

945
00:43:35,120 --> 00:43:36,914
- What'd you do?
- Uh, uh...

946
00:43:36,997 --> 00:43:39,208
Come on, I'm really good
at keeping secrets.

947
00:43:39,792 --> 00:43:41,877
- [guard 2] Nothing here, sir.
- [guard 1] Keep looking!

948
00:43:42,378 --> 00:43:43,671
The secret is...

949
00:43:44,254 --> 00:43:45,339
I'm a kid.

950
00:43:45,422 --> 00:43:46,757
What? Really?

951
00:43:47,341 --> 00:43:48,217
Mm-hmm.

952
00:43:48,300 --> 00:43:50,761
[whispering] And I kind of
tricked the Communiverse...

953
00:43:50,844 --> 00:43:52,304
- [unintelligible whispering]
- Whoa.

954
00:43:52,388 --> 00:43:53,222
What?

955
00:43:53,305 --> 00:43:56,141
- [whispering continues]
- Oh.

956
00:43:56,225 --> 00:43:57,309
No way!

957
00:43:57,393 --> 00:43:58,852
[chuckles] You're crazy.

958
00:43:58,936 --> 00:44:01,980
I know and now Grigon's
going to blow everyone up

959
00:44:02,064 --> 00:44:04,191
unless I can find
a bargaining chip.

960
00:44:04,274 --> 00:44:07,986
Something he values, but what
does he even value? [sighs]

961
00:44:08,070 --> 00:44:11,615
Well, Dad values blood, glory,
the misery of his enemies.

962
00:44:11,699 --> 00:44:12,866
Ooh.
There was this one time...

963
00:44:12,950 --> 00:44:15,577
Hold up. Grigon's your dad?

964
00:44:15,661 --> 00:44:17,913
I thought you knew.
I look just like him.

965
00:44:17,996 --> 00:44:20,541
Check it out. [grunting]

966
00:44:25,051 --> 00:44:26,428
I've been working on my back.

967
00:44:29,639 --> 00:44:33,310
Can I ask you a big favor?

968
00:44:34,352 --> 00:44:35,353
Sure.

969
00:44:35,854 --> 00:44:37,147
[Glordon]
Bargaining chip. Cool.

970
00:44:37,230 --> 00:44:38,565
I've never been
a bargaining chip before.

971
00:44:39,400 --> 00:44:41,652
I've been a liability.
A disappointment.

972
00:44:41,736 --> 00:44:44,030
- A deduction.
- Are we almost to my ship?

973
00:44:44,113 --> 00:44:47,241
Not far now. I've also been
a pillow, an enigma,

974
00:44:47,325 --> 00:44:49,076
a problem, a headache.

975
00:44:50,286 --> 00:44:52,538
- Little help, please.
- [strains]

976
00:44:52,621 --> 00:44:54,040
Lately, I've just
been ignored,

977
00:44:54,123 --> 00:44:56,751
but now my dad's finally
going to pay attention to me.

978
00:44:56,834 --> 00:44:58,753
Do your parents
pay attention to you?

979
00:44:58,836 --> 00:45:00,838
Well, my Aunt Olga
doesn't care.

980
00:45:00,921 --> 00:45:02,256
[straining]
With me out the way

981
00:45:02,340 --> 00:45:04,383
she can do
what she really wants.

982
00:45:05,343 --> 00:45:07,219
Like be an astronaut
or whatever.

983
00:45:07,303 --> 00:45:10,389
She gave up being an astronaut
or whatever for you?

984
00:45:10,473 --> 00:45:12,141
Wow. She must really love you.

985
00:45:13,267 --> 00:45:15,186
No, no, she doesn't.

986
00:45:15,269 --> 00:45:18,064
But now I'm free
to join the Communiverse,

987
00:45:18,147 --> 00:45:19,982
which is where I belong anyway

988
00:45:20,066 --> 00:45:21,734
and that's where you come in,

989
00:45:21,817 --> 00:45:23,152
bargaining chip.

990
00:45:23,235 --> 00:45:24,320
- [Elio grunts]
- Whee!

991
00:45:26,072 --> 00:45:27,948
- [Glordon] Ow.
- Oof!

992
00:45:28,032 --> 00:45:30,034
- [Glordon strains] Wiggle.
- [rumbling]

993
00:45:30,117 --> 00:45:31,535
[strains] Wiggle.

994
00:45:31,619 --> 00:45:34,246
[Helix] <i>Candidate Solís?
Sorry to bother you.</i>

995
00:45:34,330 --> 00:45:36,832
It's just that
the Hylurgian ships

996
00:45:36,916 --> 00:45:39,210
seem to be pointing
their cannons at us.

997
00:45:39,293 --> 00:45:41,295
<i>Is this part
of the negotiations?</i>

998
00:45:41,379 --> 00:45:43,839
Oh, that's just a drill.
Don't worry.

999
00:45:43,923 --> 00:45:46,008
[strains] Wiggle.

1000
00:45:46,092 --> 00:45:47,343
[Glordon laughs]

1001
00:45:48,302 --> 00:45:50,763
- Whoa. [grunts]
- Come on.

1002
00:45:50,846 --> 00:45:52,264
What are these tunnels for,
anyway?

1003
00:45:52,348 --> 00:45:55,476
Oh, these are the lava flumes.
They power the cannons.

1004
00:45:57,395 --> 00:45:59,313
Glordon, I am not fireproof!

1005
00:45:59,397 --> 00:46:00,773
Really? Why didn't
you say something?

1006
00:46:00,856 --> 00:46:01,899
Glordon!

1007
00:46:01,982 --> 00:46:04,568
It's okay.
Just get in my mouth.

1008
00:46:05,486 --> 00:46:06,862
What? No way!

1009
00:46:06,946 --> 00:46:08,030
Trust me.

1010
00:46:11,200 --> 00:46:12,868
[screaming]

1011
00:46:15,996 --> 00:46:16,997
Hmm.

1012
00:46:17,081 --> 00:46:19,291
It's, uh, actually
kind of comfy in here.

1013
00:46:19,375 --> 00:46:21,085
[Glordon] It is?
I've never been in there.

1014
00:46:21,168 --> 00:46:22,128
Hold on.

1015
00:46:22,837 --> 00:46:23,963
[laughs]

1016
00:46:27,174 --> 00:46:28,509
Yeah!

1017
00:46:31,762 --> 00:46:33,556
Ah. Refreshing.

1018
00:46:33,639 --> 00:46:35,433
[coughs]

1019
00:46:35,516 --> 00:46:36,475
[muffled] You okay?

1020
00:46:37,893 --> 00:46:38,894
[Elio] Yes!

1021
00:46:38,978 --> 00:46:40,438
Lower me down.

1022
00:46:44,150 --> 00:46:45,734
[sighs] Thanks, Glordon.

1023
00:46:45,818 --> 00:46:47,945
Eh. It's nothing. Up top.

1024
00:46:50,448 --> 00:46:53,075
How long's the flight?
Any snacks on board?

1025
00:46:56,745 --> 00:46:58,747
Ah, it's Candidate Solís!

1026
00:46:58,831 --> 00:47:01,000
I'm sure he's bringing
good news.

1027
00:47:01,083 --> 00:47:01,917
Oh.

1028
00:47:02,001 --> 00:47:03,002
Look out!

1029
00:47:03,085 --> 00:47:05,087
[slow-motion screaming]

1030
00:47:09,508 --> 00:47:11,135
I'm so excited.
I'm so excited.

1031
00:47:11,218 --> 00:47:12,136
I'm so excited.

1032
00:47:12,219 --> 00:47:13,888
- Candidate Solís?
- What's happened?

1033
00:47:13,971 --> 00:47:15,973
Ooooo, open a line
to Lord Grigon!

1034
00:47:16,056 --> 00:47:18,100
- Of course.
- Who is this?

1035
00:47:18,184 --> 00:47:19,643
<i>Who is responsible for...</i>

1036
00:47:20,603 --> 00:47:21,562
<i>- You!</i>
- [Elio] Yes.

1037
00:47:21,645 --> 00:47:24,064
It's me! The leader of Earth.

1038
00:47:24,148 --> 00:47:26,066
And the negotiation
is not over

1039
00:47:26,150 --> 00:47:28,110
because now I've got this!

1040
00:47:28,194 --> 00:47:29,028
- [Helix gasps]
- Oh, my.

1041
00:47:29,111 --> 00:47:30,362
[gasps] <i>Glordon?</i>

1042
00:47:30,446 --> 00:47:34,867
Yes, and-and pretty soon
he's going to be Glor-done.

1043
00:47:34,950 --> 00:47:36,869
Hi, Dad.
I'm a bargaining chip.

1044
00:47:36,952 --> 00:47:38,162
No. Say the other thing.

1045
00:47:38,245 --> 00:47:40,956
Oh. Help me, Father.
He overpowered me.

1046
00:47:41,040 --> 00:47:44,043
He's too strong. Too shredded.

1047
00:47:44,126 --> 00:47:45,377
Quiet, you!

1048
00:47:45,461 --> 00:47:46,712
[laughing]

1049
00:47:46,795 --> 00:47:49,924
<i>What is that unholy sound?
Stop! Stop!</i>

1050
00:47:50,007 --> 00:47:51,217
Only if you swear...

1051
00:47:51,300 --> 00:47:52,927
[whispering]
On your Hylurgian honor.

1052
00:47:53,010 --> 00:47:54,970
Oh. On your Hylurgian honor

1053
00:47:55,054 --> 00:47:58,098
to leave the Communiverse
in peace and never return.

1054
00:47:58,182 --> 00:48:00,309
<i>My Hylurgian honor?</i>

1055
00:48:00,392 --> 00:48:02,311
<i>Do you know
what you are asking?</i>

1056
00:48:02,394 --> 00:48:03,562
- <i>I will...</i>
- [laughing]

1057
00:48:04,772 --> 00:48:06,273
[groaning]

1058
00:48:07,525 --> 00:48:09,276
<i>Stop!</i>

1059
00:48:09,360 --> 00:48:11,153
<i>I-I concede!</i>

1060
00:48:13,197 --> 00:48:16,158
<i>I swear on my honor...</i>

1061
00:48:16,242 --> 00:48:17,409
[all gasp]

1062
00:48:17,493 --> 00:48:19,787
<i>You are full of surprises.</i>

1063
00:48:19,870 --> 00:48:21,038
<i>You have my vow.</i>

1064
00:48:22,289 --> 00:48:24,792
<i>I will come to collect my son,</i>

1065
00:48:24,875 --> 00:48:28,504
<i>but if even one hair
on a single nub is harmed,</i>

1066
00:48:28,587 --> 00:48:31,173
<i>you will feel my wrath.</i>

1067
00:48:33,425 --> 00:48:35,970
Well done.
I knew you had it in you.

1068
00:48:36,053 --> 00:48:37,471
- [ambassadors clamoring]
- Thank you.

1069
00:48:37,555 --> 00:48:39,557
Oh, I can't wait
for this all to be over,

1070
00:48:39,640 --> 00:48:42,268
and officially welcome you
into the fold.

1071
00:48:42,351 --> 00:48:45,145
I'm customizing your
membership badge right now.

1072
00:48:45,229 --> 00:48:46,355
Do you like the color?

1073
00:48:46,438 --> 00:48:47,273
[gasps]

1074
00:48:47,356 --> 00:48:48,440
It's beautiful.

1075
00:48:48,524 --> 00:48:50,359
And so well-deserved.

1076
00:48:50,442 --> 00:48:53,320
But first, let's prepare
for Lord Grigon's arrival.

1077
00:48:53,404 --> 00:48:54,780
Come, everyone. Chop-chop.

1078
00:48:54,863 --> 00:48:57,324
[ambassadors chattering]

1079
00:48:57,408 --> 00:48:59,118
Uh, you guys go ahead.

1080
00:48:59,201 --> 00:49:01,787
I'll take care
of the bargaining chip.

1081
00:49:01,870 --> 00:49:03,289
Very good, Candidate Solís.

1082
00:49:03,372 --> 00:49:05,541
Now, does anyone know
a good caterer?

1083
00:49:05,624 --> 00:49:07,793
[ambassadors chattering]

1084
00:49:07,876 --> 00:49:09,545
Oh, we did it.

1085
00:49:09,628 --> 00:49:12,673
[shivering]
Yeah. You were so cool.

1086
00:49:12,756 --> 00:49:14,300
Oh, you okay?

1087
00:49:14,383 --> 00:49:17,094
I've never been
outside before.

1088
00:49:17,177 --> 00:49:18,804
It's cold here.

1089
00:49:21,390 --> 00:49:24,226
[sighs] Wow!
This thing's amazing.

1090
00:49:24,310 --> 00:49:25,311
Watch this.

1091
00:49:25,394 --> 00:49:26,520
Gravity off.

1092
00:49:29,940 --> 00:49:30,941
Whoa.

1093
00:49:31,025 --> 00:49:32,610
Gravity off.

1094
00:49:34,403 --> 00:49:36,405
- Whoo-hoo!
- [Elio laughs]

1095
00:49:37,364 --> 00:49:39,700
You think this is cool?
Come on!

1096
00:49:41,660 --> 00:49:43,537
Your Wrath,
the shuttle is ready.

1097
00:49:43,621 --> 00:49:44,872
Shall we depart?

1098
00:49:44,955 --> 00:49:46,624
No, not yet.

1099
00:49:47,124 --> 00:49:50,669
The princeling was taken
because he was vulnerable...

1100
00:49:50,753 --> 00:49:53,589
exposed, soft.

1101
00:49:54,214 --> 00:49:56,050
Prepare his carapace.

1102
00:49:56,133 --> 00:49:58,218
But that will take time,
Your Bloodness...

1103
00:49:58,302 --> 00:49:59,303
Do it!

1104
00:49:59,386 --> 00:50:02,431
We will perform Glordon's
ceremony on the Communiverse

1105
00:50:03,015 --> 00:50:07,061
and they will quiver
at the full might of Hylurg!

1106
00:50:08,395 --> 00:50:09,480
[Glordon chuckles]

1107
00:50:09,563 --> 00:50:11,357
- [Elio] Ready?
- Yes.

1108
00:50:11,440 --> 00:50:12,775
No.

1109
00:50:12,858 --> 00:50:14,151
0-okay, yes!

1110
00:50:14,234 --> 00:50:15,319
On three.

1111
00:50:15,402 --> 00:50:17,237
One, two...

1112
00:50:17,321 --> 00:50:19,031
- Two and a half.
- Two and a half.

1113
00:50:19,615 --> 00:50:20,532
[in unison] Three!

1114
00:50:20,616 --> 00:50:22,034
[both screaming]

1115
00:50:23,035 --> 00:50:24,453
[♪ Upbeat music playing]

1116
00:50:24,536 --> 00:50:25,746
[both exclaim]

1117
00:50:27,456 --> 00:50:28,957
- Again?
- Heck, yeah, again.

1118
00:50:29,041 --> 00:50:30,042
[Elio] On three.

1119
00:50:30,125 --> 00:50:31,085
[in unison] One, two.

1120
00:50:31,919 --> 00:50:33,295
- [Glordon] Whoo-hoo!
- [Elio laughs]

1121
00:50:37,299 --> 00:50:38,300
- Whoo-hoo-hoo!
- [Elio laughs]

1122
00:50:41,178 --> 00:50:43,222
- Whoo!
- Yeah!

1123
00:50:43,305 --> 00:50:44,890
[retching]

1124
00:50:49,645 --> 00:50:51,105
[both laughing]

1125
00:50:51,772 --> 00:50:52,773
[Glordon gasps]

1126
00:50:53,273 --> 00:50:54,775
[♪ Upbeat music continues]

1127
00:51:06,995 --> 00:51:07,996
Whoo!

1128
00:51:10,165 --> 00:51:11,834
[chomping]

1129
00:51:15,295 --> 00:51:16,880
[retching]

1130
00:51:16,964 --> 00:51:18,465
[both laughing]

1131
00:51:19,758 --> 00:51:21,093
Ha-ha!

1132
00:51:31,186 --> 00:51:33,856
<i>Shmeepa skiddopoo-peh.</i>

1133
00:51:33,939 --> 00:51:34,940
No, no.

1134
00:51:35,023 --> 00:51:36,567
<i>Skiddopop-puh.</i>

1135
00:51:36,650 --> 00:51:37,568
Noice.

1136
00:51:37,651 --> 00:51:40,028
<i>Shmeepa skiddopop-popopop-puh!</i>

1137
00:51:41,864 --> 00:51:44,241
So, everyone speaks Elioese
on Earth?

1138
00:51:44,324 --> 00:51:45,659
Nah, just me.

1139
00:51:46,201 --> 00:51:47,578
And my parents.

1140
00:51:48,704 --> 00:51:51,206
Or at least they did.

1141
00:51:51,290 --> 00:51:52,958
My aunt's not into it,

1142
00:51:53,625 --> 00:51:57,171
but I keep using it
so I don't forget.

1143
00:51:57,254 --> 00:51:58,297
[splashes]

1144
00:51:58,380 --> 00:52:01,300
Did something happen
to your parents?

1145
00:52:02,885 --> 00:52:03,886
Yeah.

1146
00:52:05,429 --> 00:52:06,430
I'm sorry.

1147
00:52:07,181 --> 00:52:10,642
I know it's not the same,
but my mom's gone a lot.

1148
00:52:10,726 --> 00:52:12,394
Fighting the Blood Wars.

1149
00:52:13,187 --> 00:52:14,396
I miss her a ton.

1150
00:52:15,230 --> 00:52:18,442
Sometimes it feels like
Dad doesn't even want me.

1151
00:52:20,235 --> 00:52:21,320
I know what you mean.

1152
00:52:24,239 --> 00:52:27,451
The only people who wanted me
are gone.

1153
00:52:28,243 --> 00:52:30,412
But I don't know.

1154
00:52:32,414 --> 00:52:33,415
What if...

1155
00:52:35,042 --> 00:52:37,711
What if there's nothing
about me to want?

1156
00:52:39,713 --> 00:52:42,007
I thought Earth
was the problem,

1157
00:52:42,090 --> 00:52:43,175
but...

1158
00:52:44,510 --> 00:52:45,928
what if it's me?

1159
00:52:47,721 --> 00:52:49,515
Well, I like you.

1160
00:52:50,557 --> 00:52:51,850
And you seem fine to me.

1161
00:52:59,942 --> 00:53:01,151
[rumbling]

1162
00:53:05,823 --> 00:53:07,825
[♪ Ominous music playing]

1163
00:53:16,583 --> 00:53:18,460
[thrusters whine]

1164
00:53:21,588 --> 00:53:24,383
[Elio] Oh.
He brought your carapace.

1165
00:53:24,466 --> 00:53:25,759
[Glordon] I guess so?

1166
00:53:25,843 --> 00:53:27,719
But that's good, right?

1167
00:53:27,803 --> 00:53:29,888
Yeah. I mean,
it has a flame thrower,

1168
00:53:29,972 --> 00:53:31,849
a circular saw, acid gun.

1169
00:53:31,932 --> 00:53:35,811
I'll get to fight,
and conquer, and kill, and...

1170
00:53:38,188 --> 00:53:39,189
Glordon,

1171
00:53:39,690 --> 00:53:41,900
do you not want
to get into your carapace?

1172
00:53:41,984 --> 00:53:44,570
Yeah. I mean, kind of, well...

1173
00:53:44,653 --> 00:53:46,280
No, no.

1174
00:53:46,363 --> 00:53:47,823
I've been pretending
to want it,

1175
00:53:47,906 --> 00:53:49,741
but I've been living a lie!

1176
00:53:49,825 --> 00:53:51,159
[wails]

1177
00:53:53,245 --> 00:53:56,665
Once I'm installed, I'll never
get to play, or swim,

1178
00:53:56,748 --> 00:53:58,292
or do anything.

1179
00:53:58,375 --> 00:53:59,710
It'll be the worst!

1180
00:54:00,252 --> 00:54:01,837
[wailing]

1181
00:54:01,920 --> 00:54:03,797
But why didn't
you say something?

1182
00:54:03,881 --> 00:54:06,258
Because all Hylurgians
have to do it!

1183
00:54:06,341 --> 00:54:07,593
It's tradition.

1184
00:54:07,676 --> 00:54:09,219
And if I don't...

1185
00:54:09,303 --> 00:54:10,721
[sniffs]

1186
00:54:10,804 --> 00:54:12,806
...my dad would hate me.

1187
00:54:16,143 --> 00:54:18,061
[no audible dialogue]

1188
00:54:19,938 --> 00:54:22,274
Glordon, you're not
getting in there.

1189
00:54:22,357 --> 00:54:25,068
But... [sniffs]
I don't have a choice.

1190
00:54:25,652 --> 00:54:26,778
We'll figure it out.

1191
00:54:27,487 --> 00:54:28,989
I don't know how, but...

1192
00:54:31,575 --> 00:54:32,576
Oh, wait.

1193
00:54:32,659 --> 00:54:33,952
Ha!

1194
00:54:34,036 --> 00:54:34,995
What?

1195
00:54:36,288 --> 00:54:38,206
Ooh. What are we doing?

1196
00:54:38,290 --> 00:54:39,708
We're going to give your dad
what he wants.

1197
00:54:39,791 --> 00:54:40,792
Me?

1198
00:54:40,876 --> 00:54:42,210
Well, yes, but also no.

1199
00:54:43,295 --> 00:54:45,213
Cloning clay?
A-Are you sure about this?

1200
00:54:45,297 --> 00:54:46,715
Yeah. Why not?

1201
00:54:46,798 --> 00:54:48,091
[groans] I don't know.

1202
00:54:48,175 --> 00:54:49,843
Would a clone
really fool my dad?

1203
00:54:49,927 --> 00:54:51,136
He's pretty smart.

1204
00:54:51,219 --> 00:54:53,513
Oh, it's going to work.
I'll show you.

1205
00:54:53,597 --> 00:54:54,890
Ooooo? Ooooo?

1206
00:54:54,973 --> 00:54:57,309
- Yes?
- Can I check on my clone?

1207
00:54:57,392 --> 00:54:58,393
Certainly.

1208
00:54:58,477 --> 00:55:00,854
Mmm. That smells good, <i>papito.</i>

1209
00:55:00,938 --> 00:55:02,022
It's a secret recipe.

1210
00:55:02,105 --> 00:55:03,440
[Other Elio]
You're going to love it.

1211
00:55:03,523 --> 00:55:05,442
[Olga] How are you
so good at everything?

1212
00:55:05,525 --> 00:55:06,860
[both laughing]

1213
00:55:09,696 --> 00:55:11,657
[Olga] Mmm, mmm, mmm.

1214
00:55:11,740 --> 00:55:13,825
Wow. I guess it does work.

1215
00:55:13,909 --> 00:55:15,535
Okay, let's do it.

1216
00:55:16,036 --> 00:55:17,037
Yeah.

1217
00:55:17,871 --> 00:55:18,956
Yeah!

1218
00:55:19,039 --> 00:55:21,792
<i>Okay. Your dad will take
your clone back to Hylurg,</i>

1219
00:55:21,875 --> 00:55:23,377
<i>I'll become an Ambassador,</i>

1220
00:55:23,460 --> 00:55:25,295
<i>and neither of us
will have to see Hylurg,</i>

1221
00:55:25,379 --> 00:55:26,546
<i>or stupid Earth again.</i>

1222
00:55:26,630 --> 00:55:28,090
<i>It's a win-win-win.</i>

1223
00:55:28,173 --> 00:55:29,675
- [bell dings]
- [gas hissing]

1224
00:55:33,095 --> 00:55:34,513
- Whoa.
- Yes.

1225
00:55:38,600 --> 00:55:39,601
I'm Glordon!

1226
00:55:39,685 --> 00:55:41,770
Wow! Am I really that ripped?

1227
00:55:41,853 --> 00:55:42,938
You, follow us.

1228
00:55:43,021 --> 00:55:44,106
You got it.

1229
00:55:44,189 --> 00:55:45,691
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

1230
00:55:48,235 --> 00:55:50,237
You'll be safe in here.
No one else can open it.

1231
00:55:51,613 --> 00:55:53,281
All right, Glordon,
get in the ship.

1232
00:55:53,365 --> 00:55:54,324
[both] Okay.

1233
00:55:54,408 --> 00:55:55,450
I can't tell you apart.

1234
00:55:55,534 --> 00:55:56,994
- Yes!
- [Elio] Whoo-hoo!

1235
00:55:57,077 --> 00:55:58,662
Seriously, though,
which one's real?

1236
00:55:58,745 --> 00:55:59,746
Me.

1237
00:56:01,665 --> 00:56:03,917
Stay inside
and don't make a sound.

1238
00:56:06,461 --> 00:56:07,546
I'll be right back.

1239
00:56:11,925 --> 00:56:12,926
Come on.

1240
00:56:15,012 --> 00:56:17,723
You look so good. I can't
even tell the difference.

1241
00:56:18,182 --> 00:56:19,016
[Olga] Mmm.

1242
00:56:19,099 --> 00:56:20,851
I can't even
tell the difference.

1243
00:56:20,935 --> 00:56:22,019
I know.

1244
00:56:22,102 --> 00:56:24,605
Who knew yogurt is just
as yummy as butter...

1245
00:56:24,688 --> 00:56:26,690
- [Olga chuckles]
- ...and half the cholesterol?

1246
00:56:26,774 --> 00:56:27,983
[both laugh]

1247
00:56:28,067 --> 00:56:29,318
It's perfect.

1248
00:56:31,028 --> 00:56:32,071
Let me get that for you.

1249
00:56:32,154 --> 00:56:34,156
Aw. Thanks so much.

1250
00:56:35,366 --> 00:56:36,992
[humming]

1251
00:56:37,785 --> 00:56:40,454
[yawns] Well, I'm going to
turn in for the night.

1252
00:56:41,296 --> 00:56:44,173
All right. But first,
get over here, kiddo.

1253
00:56:44,257 --> 00:56:45,425
- Mwah.
- [chuckles]

1254
00:56:47,760 --> 00:56:48,928
Good night.

1255
00:56:49,012 --> 00:56:50,179
[chuckles]

1256
00:56:55,818 --> 00:56:57,236
[♪ Tense music playing]

1257
00:57:15,931 --> 00:57:16,932
Hmm.

1258
00:57:19,559 --> 00:57:21,478
[glass cracking]

1259
00:57:21,561 --> 00:57:22,896
[shatters]

1260
00:57:26,900 --> 00:57:27,901
What the?

1261
00:57:30,904 --> 00:57:32,114
[gasps]

1262
00:57:33,657 --> 00:57:34,658
[sniffing]

1263
00:57:35,367 --> 00:57:36,868
[♪ Tense music continues]

1264
00:57:53,892 --> 00:57:54,893
[gasps]

1265
00:57:57,688 --> 00:58:00,232
[♪ Ominous music playing]

1266
00:58:08,912 --> 00:58:09,913
[gasps]

1267
00:58:19,464 --> 00:58:20,757
[gasps]

1268
00:58:22,800 --> 00:58:24,469
Hi. We should probably talk.

1269
00:58:28,473 --> 00:58:30,141
[Questa]
And for my next trick,

1270
00:58:30,225 --> 00:58:31,518
think of a number.

1271
00:58:31,601 --> 00:58:34,229
- Uh, wait. Uh...
- [Grigon scoffs]

1272
00:58:34,312 --> 00:58:35,438
Okay, got it!

1273
00:58:35,980 --> 00:58:37,190
Yes. Yes, yes, yes.

1274
00:58:37,273 --> 00:58:39,484
[whispering] I don't know
how much longer we can stall.

1275
00:58:39,567 --> 00:58:40,652
Where is Candidate Solís?

1276
00:58:40,735 --> 00:58:43,112
I'm sure he'll be here
momentarily.

1277
00:58:43,196 --> 00:58:45,949
I sense the number is

1278
00:58:46,032 --> 00:58:47,867
- seven.
- What?

1279
00:58:47,951 --> 00:58:49,744
- Aw, she's right.
- [Grigon] Enough!

1280
00:58:50,328 --> 00:58:52,121
Where is my son?

1281
00:58:52,956 --> 00:58:54,958
He's here. He's right here.

1282
00:58:55,041 --> 00:58:56,042
Daddy.

1283
00:58:56,793 --> 00:58:58,878
- He did not abandon us.
- He's here!

1284
00:58:58,962 --> 00:59:00,505
Thank the stars.

1285
00:59:00,588 --> 00:59:04,133
Lord Grigon, we return
to you Prince Glordon.

1286
00:59:04,217 --> 00:59:06,302
My son. Did he harm you?

1287
00:59:06,386 --> 00:59:08,471
Nope. Everyone was super nice.

1288
00:59:08,555 --> 00:59:11,099
Hmm. Are you prepared
to become

1289
00:59:11,182 --> 00:59:14,060
the greatest war machine
in the universe?

1290
00:59:14,143 --> 00:59:17,522
To make your enemies tremble
at the sight of you?

1291
00:59:17,605 --> 00:59:19,232
To prove the might of the...

1292
00:59:19,315 --> 00:59:20,400
Yep! Let's do it!

1293
00:59:21,401 --> 00:59:22,694
Oh.

1294
00:59:22,777 --> 00:59:24,821
A-Actually, I had more to say,

1295
00:59:24,904 --> 00:59:27,490
but, yes,
I-I-let us get on with it.

1296
00:59:27,574 --> 00:59:28,575
[ambassadors talking]

1297
00:59:34,372 --> 00:59:35,456
[chuckles]

1298
00:59:35,540 --> 00:59:36,666
[Glordon chuckles]

1299
00:59:41,045 --> 00:59:42,797
[rhythmic pounding]

1300
00:59:48,469 --> 00:59:50,346
[Hylurgian soldiers chanting]

1301
00:59:59,522 --> 01:00:01,399
[horn blaring]

1302
01:00:01,482 --> 01:00:03,151
[chanting continues]

1303
01:00:03,234 --> 01:00:05,486
[Hylurgian soldier vocalizes]

1304
01:00:18,333 --> 01:00:19,334
[chanting, pounding stop]

1305
01:00:27,300 --> 01:00:28,301
[pulsing]

1306
01:00:30,854 --> 01:00:32,522
[beeping]

1307
01:00:32,606 --> 01:00:33,482
[continuous beep]

1308
01:00:34,399 --> 01:00:35,734
[electronic noises]

1309
01:00:37,569 --> 01:00:38,612
Whoo!

1310
01:00:39,112 --> 01:00:40,113
Oh, yeah.

1311
01:00:40,197 --> 01:00:41,198
[grunts]

1312
01:00:42,491 --> 01:00:44,117
- Whew.
- [ambassadors] Whew.

1313
01:00:46,669 --> 01:00:49,255
Witness the power of Hylurg.

1314
01:00:50,131 --> 01:00:51,215
[Grigon] Witness!

1315
01:00:51,299 --> 01:00:53,050
- What a good show.
- Very impressive.

1316
01:00:53,134 --> 01:00:54,802
That's right.

1317
01:00:56,012 --> 01:00:57,597
As you have kept your word,

1318
01:00:57,680 --> 01:01:01,642
I will keep mine and leave
this place, never to return.

1319
01:01:01,726 --> 01:01:03,978
Hylurgians, fall back.

1320
01:01:04,979 --> 01:01:06,522
[Questa] Candidate Solís,
you did it!

1321
01:01:06,606 --> 01:01:08,774
- [all clamoring]
- [Helix] Well done.

1322
01:01:08,858 --> 01:01:10,276
What an exceptional specimen.

1323
01:01:10,359 --> 01:01:11,694
You good, Son?

1324
01:01:11,777 --> 01:01:14,739
Oh, yeah. I can't wait
to make endless war

1325
01:01:14,822 --> 01:01:17,033
and pillage the unworthy
and bring eternal night...

1326
01:01:17,116 --> 01:01:20,620
May I have the honor
of joining the Communiverse?

1327
01:01:21,329 --> 01:01:24,707
The honor would be ours,
Candidate Solís.

1328
01:01:24,790 --> 01:01:27,793
Or should I say,
Ambassador Solís.

1329
01:01:27,877 --> 01:01:29,378
- You're one of us now.
- You're amazing!

1330
01:01:29,462 --> 01:01:30,463
- [Tegmen] I like you.
- [ambassador 3] Welcome!

1331
01:01:36,177 --> 01:01:37,219
[explosion]

1332
01:01:41,682 --> 01:01:43,017
Ah.

1333
01:01:43,100 --> 01:01:44,226
It was a clone.

1334
01:01:44,310 --> 01:01:46,270
Where is my son?

1335
01:01:46,354 --> 01:01:48,022
But... [grunts]

1336
01:01:48,606 --> 01:01:49,565
How could you tell?

1337
01:01:49,649 --> 01:01:52,693
A father always knows.

1338
01:01:54,528 --> 01:01:56,697
You, read his mind.

1339
01:01:56,781 --> 01:01:58,282
Find the truth.

1340
01:01:58,366 --> 01:01:59,367
No.

1341
01:02:00,159 --> 01:02:01,243
Unhand me!

1342
01:02:01,327 --> 01:02:02,411
I'm so sorry.

1343
01:02:02,495 --> 01:02:03,788
No. [straining]

1344
01:02:03,871 --> 01:02:04,872
No.

1345
01:02:06,624 --> 01:02:09,126
No, no. No, no, please. No!

1346
01:02:09,210 --> 01:02:10,211
[gasps]

1347
01:02:13,172 --> 01:02:15,174
What? What did you see?

1348
01:02:15,257 --> 01:02:19,470
Your son is in a diplomatic
ship in the docking bay.

1349
01:02:19,553 --> 01:02:21,013
[Grigon] Send the troops!

1350
01:02:24,517 --> 01:02:26,227
[Glordon humming]

1351
01:02:26,310 --> 01:02:27,853
Oh, more pudding, Elio?

1352
01:02:27,937 --> 01:02:29,355
Why, thank you, Glordon!

1353
01:02:29,438 --> 01:02:30,648
- [thudding]
- [Glordon gasps]

1354
01:02:35,444 --> 01:02:36,445
[gasps]

1355
01:02:38,489 --> 01:02:39,573
Elio?

1356
01:02:40,616 --> 01:02:41,742
[grunting]

1357
01:02:41,826 --> 01:02:42,827
[yelps]

1358
01:02:42,910 --> 01:02:44,870
[ship] <i>You have selected
a map of our coordinates.</i>

1359
01:02:44,954 --> 01:02:46,914
<i>Neck pillow. Lip balm.
A breath mint.</i>

1360
01:02:46,998 --> 01:02:47,832
Mmm.

1361
01:02:47,915 --> 01:02:49,000
[ship] <i>Destination...</i>

1362
01:02:49,083 --> 01:02:50,209
[Elio's voice] <i>Uh, Earth.</i>

1363
01:02:50,292 --> 01:02:52,086
[ship] <i>Confirm or cancel?</i>

1364
01:02:52,169 --> 01:02:54,255
What? Confirm?

1365
01:03:02,221 --> 01:03:05,266
Ooooo, open a portal to Earth.

1366
01:03:07,309 --> 01:03:08,644
What are you doing?

1367
01:03:08,728 --> 01:03:11,147
Will you tell them, or must I?

1368
01:03:12,773 --> 01:03:13,774
Please don't.

1369
01:03:14,358 --> 01:03:16,110
He is not the leader of Earth.

1370
01:03:16,193 --> 01:03:17,194
[ambassadors exclaiming]

1371
01:03:17,278 --> 01:03:19,321
He is not the leader
of anything.

1372
01:03:19,822 --> 01:03:21,240
He is just

1373
01:03:21,323 --> 01:03:22,324
a child.

1374
01:03:22,908 --> 01:03:23,868
- What?
- Oh, no.

1375
01:03:23,951 --> 01:03:24,952
- I do not understand.
- No.

1376
01:03:25,036 --> 01:03:26,829
She's... She's wrong.

1377
01:03:27,455 --> 01:03:30,082
- I am the leader of Earth.
- [ambassadors gasp]

1378
01:03:31,876 --> 01:03:33,335
I can still help!

1379
01:03:33,419 --> 01:03:35,796
Just please,
please let me stay.

1380
01:03:36,464 --> 01:03:37,798
He is not there!

1381
01:03:37,882 --> 01:03:39,300
- What?
- But I saw him!

1382
01:03:39,383 --> 01:03:40,760
We are as surprised as you.

1383
01:03:40,843 --> 01:03:42,011
Arrest them all!

1384
01:03:42,094 --> 01:03:46,140
The Communiverse is now
under Hylurgian control.

1385
01:03:54,231 --> 01:03:55,149
[shouting]

1386
01:03:55,232 --> 01:03:57,109
[Auva] Don't touch me. Stop!

1387
01:03:57,193 --> 01:03:58,194
[ambassador 2]
We can sort this out!

1388
01:03:58,277 --> 01:04:00,821
- [Tegmen] Ouch.
- It's his fault, not ours!

1389
01:04:00,905 --> 01:04:03,699
Liar! Betrayer! Coward!

1390
01:04:03,783 --> 01:04:05,034
Leave! Now!

1391
01:04:05,910 --> 01:04:06,869
I'm so sorry.

1392
01:04:06,952 --> 01:04:07,953
You've done enough!

1393
01:04:08,996 --> 01:04:10,956
[distorted] No!

1394
01:04:11,040 --> 01:04:12,541
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

1395
01:04:20,091 --> 01:04:21,926
[♪ Melancholic music playing]

1396
01:04:23,969 --> 01:04:27,640
Tear this place apart
until you find my son!

1397
01:04:31,393 --> 01:04:32,728
[yells]

1398
01:04:36,107 --> 01:04:36,941
[gasping]

1399
01:04:38,359 --> 01:04:39,985
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

1400
01:04:49,286 --> 01:04:50,913
[inhaling, coughing]

1401
01:04:56,043 --> 01:04:57,086
No. [breathing heavily]

1402
01:05:05,761 --> 01:05:07,429
[♪ Melancholic music playing]

1403
01:05:11,183 --> 01:05:12,434
Don't leave me.

1404
01:05:15,813 --> 01:05:16,939
Please.

1405
01:05:32,913 --> 01:05:34,456
[crying]

1406
01:05:41,589 --> 01:05:42,923
[Other Elio giggling]

1407
01:05:46,010 --> 01:05:48,262
- [gasps]
- Oh, I'll take that.

1408
01:05:48,345 --> 01:05:49,346
Thanks, kiddo.

1409
01:05:55,853 --> 01:05:58,314
[Olga] Shoot.
I left the, um... That, uh...

1410
01:05:58,397 --> 01:05:59,940
I know what it is.
Be right back.

1411
01:06:00,024 --> 01:06:01,442
- Thank you.
- [Other Elio laughs]

1412
01:06:14,997 --> 01:06:16,290
[speaking Spanish]

1413
01:06:19,668 --> 01:06:21,086
[in English]
You couldn't find it, huh?

1414
01:06:21,170 --> 01:06:22,463
Would you toss me those?

1415
01:06:42,524 --> 01:06:43,609
Come on!

1416
01:06:44,276 --> 01:06:45,653
Stupid flashlight!

1417
01:06:47,947 --> 01:06:48,948
Sorry.

1418
01:06:49,490 --> 01:06:50,324
[sighs]

1419
01:06:53,118 --> 01:06:54,370
Are you okay?

1420
01:06:54,453 --> 01:06:56,705
No. I feel crazy!

1421
01:06:56,789 --> 01:06:57,831
I'm on the beach

1422
01:06:57,915 --> 01:07:01,252
trying to make contact
with I don't know what.

1423
01:07:04,463 --> 01:07:05,464
I just...

1424
01:07:07,591 --> 01:07:08,801
feel so...

1425
01:07:10,386 --> 01:07:11,387
alone.

1426
01:07:13,639 --> 01:07:15,307
[sighs]
You wouldn't understand.

1427
01:07:26,402 --> 01:07:27,403
Actually,

1428
01:07:28,904 --> 01:07:30,072
I do.

1429
01:07:34,994 --> 01:07:36,245
[crackling]

1430
01:08:01,236 --> 01:08:02,237
[Olga sighs]

1431
01:08:02,988 --> 01:08:04,406
[inhales deeply] Oh.

1432
01:08:08,702 --> 01:08:10,662
I didn't think you'd miss me.

1433
01:08:12,205 --> 01:08:13,582
I missed you.

1434
01:08:14,624 --> 01:08:17,419
I've missed
everything about you.

1435
01:08:18,295 --> 01:08:19,588
But...

1436
01:08:20,297 --> 01:08:22,716
this isn't the life
you wanted.

1437
01:08:25,802 --> 01:08:27,512
The only thing I want

1438
01:08:28,555 --> 01:08:29,556
is you.

1439
01:08:31,266 --> 01:08:32,267
[sighs]

1440
01:08:36,688 --> 01:08:37,689
[sighs]

1441
01:08:41,484 --> 01:08:44,029
- [helicopter whirring]
- [Other Elio panting]

1442
01:08:44,946 --> 01:08:46,698
<i>Tía</i> Olga! Oh.

1443
01:08:46,781 --> 01:08:48,909
Oh, hey, you're back!

1444
01:08:48,992 --> 01:08:50,035
Whew.

1445
01:08:50,118 --> 01:08:52,120
Something's going on
at the base.

1446
01:08:57,417 --> 01:08:58,418
[sirens]

1447
01:09:03,215 --> 01:09:04,257
[gasps]

1448
01:09:04,341 --> 01:09:06,802
[Elio] Wait.
That's my spaceship.

1449
01:09:06,885 --> 01:09:08,595
- Glordon's in there!
- Who?

1450
01:09:08,679 --> 01:09:09,930
My friend.

1451
01:09:10,268 --> 01:09:11,770
- You made a friend?
- You made a friend? Nice.

1452
01:09:11,853 --> 01:09:14,522
Yeah, and he needs our help.
You have clearance, right?

1453
01:09:14,606 --> 01:09:16,066
Not for this.

1454
01:09:16,566 --> 01:09:19,235
[groans] There's got to be
some way to get in there.

1455
01:09:19,319 --> 01:09:20,528
0-okay, okay. Let me think.

1456
01:09:22,030 --> 01:09:23,406
[Elio groans]

1457
01:09:24,407 --> 01:09:25,742
Well, if you don't
need me anymore,

1458
01:09:25,825 --> 01:09:27,869
I will begin
my decomposition process.

1459
01:09:27,953 --> 01:09:29,412
Feel free to spread me
over a plant

1460
01:09:29,496 --> 01:09:30,789
as nutritious fertilizer.

1461
01:09:30,872 --> 01:09:32,874
[warbling]

1462
01:09:34,459 --> 01:09:35,627
[both] Wait!

1463
01:09:37,087 --> 01:09:39,172
- [soldiers clamoring]
- [tires screech]

1464
01:09:40,924 --> 01:09:42,133
[bell rings]

1465
01:09:42,217 --> 01:09:43,802
They, uh, mention what it is?

1466
01:09:43,885 --> 01:09:46,846
Negative. But AARO's here
and NASA's on the way.

1467
01:09:48,890 --> 01:09:51,101
Is it extraterrestrial?

1468
01:09:51,184 --> 01:09:53,269
[scoffs]
What, like little green men?

1469
01:09:53,353 --> 01:09:55,021
Don't tell me you believe
in that stuff.

1470
01:09:55,105 --> 01:09:56,106
[echoing laugh]

1471
01:09:58,525 --> 01:09:59,734
Who's there?

1472
01:09:59,818 --> 01:10:01,152
[♪ Tense music playing]

1473
01:10:03,363 --> 01:10:04,531
[sighs] It's a kid.

1474
01:10:04,614 --> 01:10:05,824
Hey, you shouldn't be here.

1475
01:10:06,408 --> 01:10:07,826
[neck cracks]

1476
01:10:10,537 --> 01:10:12,664
Can you help me?

1477
01:10:12,747 --> 01:10:14,124
[♪ Tense music continues]

1478
01:10:23,091 --> 01:10:24,300
Huh?

1479
01:10:24,384 --> 01:10:27,178
[distorted]
I don't feel so good.

1480
01:10:27,262 --> 01:10:28,680
[screaming]

1481
01:10:28,763 --> 01:10:30,557
- Get it off me!
- [soldiers screaming]

1482
01:10:30,640 --> 01:10:31,975
- Get it off me!
- [clamoring]

1483
01:10:34,644 --> 01:10:35,895
It's in my mouth!

1484
01:10:35,979 --> 01:10:36,938
Why is it sour?

1485
01:10:37,022 --> 01:10:38,148
It's on me too!

1486
01:10:38,231 --> 01:10:39,733
[soldier 2] Help! Help!

1487
01:10:39,816 --> 01:10:42,152
[soldiers clamoring]

1488
01:10:43,695 --> 01:10:45,196
Thank you for your service.

1489
01:10:49,868 --> 01:10:51,619
- [indistinct radio chatter]
- [scientists grunting]

1490
01:11:06,468 --> 01:11:08,011
[♪ Uplifting music playing]

1491
01:11:12,474 --> 01:11:13,600
[muffled shout]

1492
01:11:14,851 --> 01:11:16,770
[panting]

1493
01:11:18,396 --> 01:11:19,814
[beeping]

1494
01:11:19,898 --> 01:11:21,107
[door hisses]

1495
01:11:29,491 --> 01:11:30,909
[gasps] Glordon!

1496
01:11:30,992 --> 01:11:32,827
[Glordon panting]

1497
01:11:32,911 --> 01:11:37,373
[panting and wheezing]

1498
01:11:37,457 --> 01:11:39,209
Is that your friend?

1499
01:11:39,793 --> 01:11:40,960
[distorted] Elio?

1500
01:11:41,044 --> 01:11:43,296
[distorted]
What are you doing here?

1501
01:11:43,922 --> 01:11:45,173
What are you doing here?

1502
01:11:45,256 --> 01:11:47,008
Why didn't you stay
where I told you?

1503
01:11:47,092 --> 01:11:48,343
I'm sorry.

1504
01:11:48,426 --> 01:11:51,763
[distorted] I accidentally
turned on the ship.

1505
01:11:52,514 --> 01:11:54,682
- [Glordon growling]
- [beeping fading]

1506
01:11:56,476 --> 01:11:58,228
Glordon? Glordon!

1507
01:11:58,311 --> 01:12:00,230
- Is he sick?
- His disc is broken.

1508
01:12:00,313 --> 01:12:01,648
It's too cold for him here!

1509
01:12:01,731 --> 01:12:02,816
- Hey!
- [both gasp]

1510
01:12:02,899 --> 01:12:05,527
Put your hands up!
Back away from the specimen.

1511
01:12:05,610 --> 01:12:07,028
[panting]

1512
01:12:07,112 --> 01:12:08,238
I said, back away! Now!

1513
01:12:09,408 --> 01:12:12,411
Shmeegle shmarpie blop.

1514
01:12:12,495 --> 01:12:14,664
[gasps] You learned Elioese?

1515
01:12:14,747 --> 01:12:17,291
[in Elioese]

1516
01:12:18,501 --> 01:12:19,418
Hey, what are you saying?

1517
01:12:23,631 --> 01:12:25,549
- Oh, you mean "glöp."
- Stop that!

1518
01:12:26,684 --> 01:12:27,518
[all grunt]

1519
01:12:28,978 --> 01:12:29,979
Gun it!

1520
01:12:48,706 --> 01:12:50,124
[panting]

1521
01:12:50,625 --> 01:12:52,752
Oh, my gosh. Oh...

1522
01:12:53,253 --> 01:12:54,629
This is so...

1523
01:12:54,712 --> 01:12:55,546
Oh, my gosh.

1524
01:12:55,630 --> 01:12:56,464
[Glordon growls]

1525
01:12:56,547 --> 01:12:57,632
Hold on, Glordon.

1526
01:12:57,715 --> 01:12:59,259
Olga, you got to drive!

1527
01:12:59,342 --> 01:13:00,843
- B-But how?
- Please!

1528
01:13:01,386 --> 01:13:02,804
[ship] <i>Welcome, guest pilot!</i>

1529
01:13:02,887 --> 01:13:04,681
[groaning]

1530
01:13:05,181 --> 01:13:06,349
Give me your jacket.

1531
01:13:08,017 --> 01:13:11,062
I'm so sorry, Glordon.
This is all my fault.

1532
01:13:12,772 --> 01:13:13,856
[growls]

1533
01:13:13,940 --> 01:13:15,233
Don't worry.

1534
01:13:15,316 --> 01:13:16,734
I'm going to get you home.

1535
01:13:17,992 --> 01:13:19,493
Ship, get us
to the Communiverse.

1536
01:13:20,995 --> 01:13:23,372
[ship] <i>Hyper-speed unavailable,
path blocked.</i>

1537
01:13:23,456 --> 01:13:25,291
What? It's totally clear.

1538
01:13:25,374 --> 01:13:27,460
[ship] <i>I said,
"Hyper-speed unavailable,</i>

1539
01:13:27,543 --> 01:13:28,544
<i>path blocked."</i>

1540
01:13:28,628 --> 01:13:29,629
Oh, come on!

1541
01:13:35,135 --> 01:13:36,219
[Elio groans]

1542
01:13:36,302 --> 01:13:37,303
- What?
- Shh.

1543
01:13:39,973 --> 01:13:41,015
[both exclaim]

1544
01:13:42,016 --> 01:13:43,601
[gasps]
We're in a debris field.

1545
01:13:44,602 --> 01:13:46,479
- Let's just get out of here.
- No!

1546
01:13:47,397 --> 01:13:48,773
These objects are faster
than bullets.

1547
01:13:48,857 --> 01:13:50,191
But this is what you do.

1548
01:13:50,275 --> 01:13:51,609
From the ground.

1549
01:13:51,693 --> 01:13:53,361
I don't know where
the debris's coming from.

1550
01:13:53,445 --> 01:13:55,321
I-I need altitudes,
velo... [gasps]

1551
01:13:55,405 --> 01:13:58,867
[sighs] If I could just
contact someone on the ground.

1552
01:13:58,950 --> 01:14:00,910
[groans]
But the base is on lockdown.

1553
01:14:00,994 --> 01:14:03,496
Maybe someone with a--
with a ham radio.

1554
01:14:03,580 --> 01:14:04,581
- I don't know!
- [gasps]

1555
01:14:05,999 --> 01:14:07,000
Elio?

1556
01:14:07,834 --> 01:14:10,170
Bro, I bet that UFO was real.

1557
01:14:10,754 --> 01:14:12,422
Oh, what if they're here
for food

1558
01:14:12,505 --> 01:14:14,257
and the only thing they eat
are hamsters?

1559
01:14:14,883 --> 01:14:16,009
I'm fine with that.

1560
01:14:16,885 --> 01:14:18,887
[mysterious sounds]

1561
01:14:24,267 --> 01:14:26,519
[Elio] <i>PXLOL, please respond.</i>

1562
01:14:26,603 --> 01:14:27,896
<i>PXLOL, come in!</i>

1563
01:14:27,979 --> 01:14:29,898
Hello? This is PXLOL.

1564
01:14:29,981 --> 01:14:31,399
Bryce! Uh...

1565
01:14:31,483 --> 01:14:33,443
This is Elio.

1566
01:14:34,277 --> 01:14:36,863
[Bryce] <i>Solís?
I'm sorry about what happened.</i>

1567
01:14:36,946 --> 01:14:39,282
Caleb can be
a real butt sometimes.

1568
01:14:39,365 --> 01:14:42,577
It's okay, I was a butt too.

1569
01:14:43,203 --> 01:14:44,996
Look, you might not
believe this,

1570
01:14:45,079 --> 01:14:46,164
but we're in an alien ship
that just...

1571
01:14:46,247 --> 01:14:47,582
That's you? Aw, man!

1572
01:14:47,665 --> 01:14:49,209
There's a lot of radio chatter
about that.

1573
01:14:49,292 --> 01:14:50,126
[Elio] <i>Yeah, that's us.</i>

1574
01:14:50,210 --> 01:14:51,419
<i>We're trying to fly
through debris,</i>

1575
01:14:51,503 --> 01:14:52,962
but we need to know
where it's coming...

1576
01:14:53,046 --> 01:14:53,880
[both scream]

1577
01:14:53,963 --> 01:14:55,840
How's your math? Physics?
Are you good at physics?

1578
01:14:55,924 --> 01:14:56,800
Whoa. Uh...

1579
01:14:56,883 --> 01:14:59,886
Bryce, I really
need your help.

1580
01:14:59,969 --> 01:15:01,221
<i>Please.</i>

1581
01:15:01,304 --> 01:15:03,389
I don't know anything
about debris,

1582
01:15:03,932 --> 01:15:05,225
but I know someone who does.

1583
01:15:05,734 --> 01:15:08,153
<i>He's a legend
in my radio group.</i>

1584
01:15:08,236 --> 01:15:11,156
<i>The boss. The eyes in the sky.
He's...</i>

1585
01:15:11,239 --> 01:15:13,867
Melmac reporting for duty!

1586
01:15:13,950 --> 01:15:16,036
I'll take it from here, PXLOL!

1587
01:15:16,119 --> 01:15:18,663
Elio, you better come back
in one piece, okay?

1588
01:15:18,747 --> 01:15:19,831
I'll tell you all about it.

1589
01:15:19,915 --> 01:15:22,167
Thank you, Melmac,
I owe you a huge...

1590
01:15:22,250 --> 01:15:23,335
[Melmac]
<i>Never mind that, Major.</i>

1591
01:15:23,418 --> 01:15:26,296
A Master of Ham
always helps in a jam.

1592
01:15:26,380 --> 01:15:27,214
Ha!

1593
01:15:27,297 --> 01:15:29,299
Let's get you
through this debris field.

1594
01:15:29,383 --> 01:15:30,384
I'm pulling up
the network now.

1595
01:15:30,467 --> 01:15:31,301
Get ready.

1596
01:15:31,385 --> 01:15:32,761
We need a fixed target.

1597
01:15:32,844 --> 01:15:34,012
[gasps] Orion's belt.

1598
01:15:34,096 --> 01:15:35,597
Perfect.
Drive straight toward it,

1599
01:15:35,680 --> 01:15:37,057
- and be ready to dodge.
- [Elio] Okay.

1600
01:15:37,140 --> 01:15:39,976
Uh, ship, can you, um--
can you project a grid?

1601
01:15:40,811 --> 01:15:43,188
Okay. Melmac,
anything out there?

1602
01:15:43,271 --> 01:15:44,898
Hurry, before we're
out of range!

1603
01:15:44,981 --> 01:15:47,025
Uh... Okay. Large rocket body!

1604
01:15:47,109 --> 01:15:48,693
Altitude, 407 kilometers,

1605
01:15:48,777 --> 01:15:50,153
<i>velocity, 766.</i>

1606
01:15:50,237 --> 01:15:51,238
Got it.

1607
01:15:51,321 --> 01:15:52,155
There.

1608
01:15:52,239 --> 01:15:53,323
Where? I-I don't see it!

1609
01:15:53,407 --> 01:15:54,574
Just pull back. Now!

1610
01:15:54,658 --> 01:15:55,784
[screams]

1611
01:15:56,827 --> 01:16:00,247
Another one! 788 kilometers,
velocity, 7.46.

1612
01:16:00,330 --> 01:16:02,165
- Climb fast! Now!
- Roger!

1613
01:16:03,875 --> 01:16:05,752
Whoo! We are going ham!

1614
01:16:05,836 --> 01:16:06,878
[Melmac laughs]

1615
01:16:06,962 --> 01:16:08,004
You're doing great.

1616
01:16:08,088 --> 01:16:09,131
Melmac, keep them coming.

1617
01:16:09,214 --> 01:16:10,924
Major, you're leaving
the comm window.

1618
01:16:11,007 --> 01:16:12,008
Just stay on this frequency.

1619
01:16:12,682 --> 01:16:14,225
<i>Stay... frequency...</i>

1620
01:16:14,308 --> 01:16:16,102
- Melmac? Melmac?
- [beeping]

1621
01:16:18,646 --> 01:16:21,024
[ship] <i>Shields at 80%.</i>

1622
01:16:21,107 --> 01:16:22,066
[Glordon groaning]

1623
01:16:23,526 --> 01:16:24,527
Glordon.

1624
01:16:25,111 --> 01:16:26,195
Is anyone there?

1625
01:16:26,279 --> 01:16:29,282
Please, anyone? Mayday!
Mayday! Come in. Come in!

1626
01:16:29,949 --> 01:16:30,992
[both exclaim]

1627
01:16:31,951 --> 01:16:33,870
- [ship] <i>Shields at 60%.</i>
- [alarm beeping]

1628
01:16:33,953 --> 01:16:35,747
[both grunt]

1629
01:16:38,916 --> 01:16:40,126
[both grunt]

1630
01:16:41,669 --> 01:16:43,755
[ship] <i>Shields at 41%.</i>

1631
01:16:47,967 --> 01:16:48,801
[thud]

1632
01:16:48,885 --> 01:16:50,595
- [ship] <i>Shields at 23%.</i>
- [Elio grunts]

1633
01:16:50,678 --> 01:16:53,514
Mayday! Mayday!
Come in. Come in!

1634
01:16:53,598 --> 01:16:55,516
- Hello?
- [ship] <i>Shields at 16%.</i>

1635
01:16:55,600 --> 01:16:56,476
[both exclaim]

1636
01:16:56,559 --> 01:16:58,644
- Is anyone out there?
- [Elio grunts]

1637
01:16:58,728 --> 01:17:00,188
[echoing] Can anyone hear us?

1638
01:17:14,035 --> 01:17:16,037
- <i>This is...</i>
- [radio crackles]

1639
01:17:16,120 --> 01:17:17,246
<i>...Senegal.</i>

1640
01:17:19,332 --> 01:17:20,249
[ham operator 1] <i>Bonjour.</i>

1641
01:17:20,333 --> 01:17:21,709
<i>This is Masters of Ham
in Senegal.</i>

1642
01:17:21,793 --> 01:17:23,336
Yes, yes. We read you.

1643
01:17:23,419 --> 01:17:26,089
[ham operator 1] <i>Large debris
at 1,300 kilometers,</i>

1644
01:17:26,172 --> 01:17:27,965
<i>velocity, 7.2.</i>

1645
01:17:28,049 --> 01:17:29,717
Pull back! Hard!

1646
01:17:31,260 --> 01:17:32,220
Thank you. Thank you.

1647
01:17:32,303 --> 01:17:33,846
[ham operator 1] <i>Masters
of Ham at your service.</i>

1648
01:17:33,930 --> 01:17:35,431
[on radio]
<i>This is Giulia from Italia.</i>

1649
01:17:35,515 --> 01:17:36,891
This is awesome!

1650
01:17:36,974 --> 01:17:38,935
- <i>2,224, velocity 6.81.</i>
- Right.

1651
01:17:39,936 --> 01:17:41,270
<i>This is Anoush in Armenia.</i>

1652
01:17:41,354 --> 01:17:43,106
<i>- Velocity, 6.75.</i>
- Right!

1653
01:17:43,189 --> 01:17:44,232
[ham operator 3] <i>Namaste.</i>

1654
01:17:44,315 --> 01:17:45,608
<i>- This is Vikram from Mumbai.</i>
- Climb!

1655
01:17:45,691 --> 01:17:47,610
[Vikram] <i>Debris at 2, 753,</i>

1656
01:17:47,693 --> 01:17:49,904
- <i>velocity, 6.61.</i>
- Left!

1657
01:17:49,987 --> 01:17:52,156
<i>-This is Hoang in Vietnam.
- Velocity 6...</i>

1658
01:17:52,240 --> 01:17:53,658
[ham operator 4]
<i>Konnichiwa from Japan.</i>

1659
01:17:53,741 --> 01:17:54,951
<i>You can do this!</i>

1660
01:17:55,034 --> 01:17:57,203
<i>- You're going to be okay.
- You're not alone.</i>

1661
01:17:57,286 --> 01:17:58,621
- <i>Go, go, go!</i>
- [laughs] <i>Come on, kid!</i>

1662
01:17:58,704 --> 01:18:00,331
<i>-Keep going!
- You're almost there!</i>

1663
01:18:00,414 --> 01:18:02,667
[ham operators cheering]

1664
01:18:02,750 --> 01:18:04,252
[ham operator 5]
<i>There's one more piece!</i>

1665
01:18:04,335 --> 01:18:05,378
<i>Move, move, move!</i>

1666
01:18:05,461 --> 01:18:06,337
- Which way?
- I don't know.

1667
01:18:07,463 --> 01:18:08,673
[low rumbling]

1668
01:18:12,176 --> 01:18:13,386
[both grunting]

1669
01:18:22,270 --> 01:18:23,271
[ship] <i>Path cleared.</i>

1670
01:18:23,980 --> 01:18:25,857
[sighs, laughs]

1671
01:18:28,568 --> 01:18:30,278
[♪ Hopeful music playing]

1672
01:18:36,742 --> 01:18:38,411
[gasps] Glordon?

1673
01:18:40,997 --> 01:18:42,290
[control panel beeping]

1674
01:18:42,373 --> 01:18:44,000
[ship] <i>Engaging hyper-speed.</i>

1675
01:18:47,795 --> 01:18:49,213
[♪ Dramatic music playing]

1676
01:18:57,889 --> 01:18:58,973
[grunts]

1677
01:19:00,725 --> 01:19:01,934
[both groaning]

1678
01:19:02,018 --> 01:19:03,060
[gasps]

1679
01:19:04,270 --> 01:19:05,563
[♪ Ominous music playing]

1680
01:19:10,776 --> 01:19:12,612
Help us. Please.

1681
01:19:13,487 --> 01:19:14,906
- [Olga] Elio.
- [Elio] Glordon. No!

1682
01:19:14,989 --> 01:19:16,657
[Olga]Get <i>off</i> me! [grunts]

1683
01:19:17,867 --> 01:19:19,285
[Elio struggling]

1684
01:19:24,832 --> 01:19:26,417
[crying]

1685
01:19:29,045 --> 01:19:30,046
Glordon.

1686
01:19:31,547 --> 01:19:32,715
Glordon, wake up.

1687
01:19:36,928 --> 01:19:37,929
No.

1688
01:19:38,930 --> 01:19:40,431
I can't lose you too.

1689
01:19:46,354 --> 01:19:47,980
- [roars]
- [gasps]

1690
01:19:48,064 --> 01:19:49,523
No!

1691
01:19:59,242 --> 01:20:00,409
[roaring]

1692
01:20:12,129 --> 01:20:14,715
[growling]

1693
01:20:22,598 --> 01:20:23,599
[gasps]

1694
01:20:28,437 --> 01:20:30,022
[sighs]

1695
01:20:34,318 --> 01:20:35,528
[Glordon grunts]

1696
01:20:36,320 --> 01:20:38,072
[both sigh]

1697
01:20:41,284 --> 01:20:43,619
[both growl]

1698
01:20:45,746 --> 01:20:47,039
[speaks Hylurgian]

1699
01:20:54,922 --> 01:20:56,966
Explain yourselves.

1700
01:20:59,302 --> 01:21:00,303
Huh?

1701
01:21:00,386 --> 01:21:02,888
I-- I can't.

1702
01:21:02,972 --> 01:21:04,640
Just tell him.

1703
01:21:05,308 --> 01:21:06,934
He loves you.

1704
01:21:07,476 --> 01:21:09,353
Look how much
he wanted you back.

1705
01:21:11,022 --> 01:21:12,315
[gulps]

1706
01:21:13,983 --> 01:21:14,984
I-I...

1707
01:21:15,735 --> 01:21:18,404
I don't want to be
a war machine.

1708
01:21:21,574 --> 01:21:23,242
[sighs]

1709
01:21:23,993 --> 01:21:25,619
You already know?

1710
01:21:26,245 --> 01:21:27,246
Yes.

1711
01:21:29,165 --> 01:21:32,335
I may not always
understand you,

1712
01:21:33,961 --> 01:21:35,671
but I still love you.

1713
01:21:40,634 --> 01:21:41,635
[sighs]

1714
01:21:43,679 --> 01:21:45,973
[stammers]
It's a loose swaddle.

1715
01:21:46,057 --> 01:21:48,184
I do not have
your mother's touch.

1716
01:21:48,267 --> 01:21:49,518
You did great.

1717
01:21:51,729 --> 01:21:55,024
I have never uttered
these words before,

1718
01:21:56,108 --> 01:21:57,693
but I am...

1719
01:21:57,777 --> 01:21:59,945
[elongated] ...sorry.

1720
01:22:00,446 --> 01:22:01,530
[sighs]

1721
01:22:01,614 --> 01:22:02,698
Release them all.

1722
01:22:04,200 --> 01:22:05,951
[ambassadors chattering]

1723
01:22:08,996 --> 01:22:10,498
[♪ Uplifting music playing]

1724
01:22:29,558 --> 01:22:32,978
[Questa] Congratulations,
Ambassador Solís!

1725
01:22:34,772 --> 01:22:36,816
But I-I lied to you!

1726
01:22:36,899 --> 01:22:40,528
And then you sacrificed
yourself to save another.

1727
01:22:41,153 --> 01:22:45,533
You behaved as admirably
as any real planetary leader.

1728
01:22:45,616 --> 01:22:47,284
And you did bring peace.

1729
01:22:47,868 --> 01:22:49,036
Eventually.

1730
01:22:49,120 --> 01:22:51,122
You have earned
your place here.

1731
01:22:51,705 --> 01:22:52,790
I could stay?

1732
01:22:52,873 --> 01:22:54,542
Yes, yes, yes!

1733
01:22:57,711 --> 01:22:59,422
- [Elio laughs]
- [Naos] Excellent.

1734
01:23:00,423 --> 01:23:01,674
[Glordon]
We can hang out every day.

1735
01:23:01,757 --> 01:23:03,634
[chattering continues,
distorted]

1736
01:23:03,717 --> 01:23:05,386
[sighs]

1737
01:23:30,494 --> 01:23:32,538
[♪ Melancholic music playing]

1738
01:24:03,777 --> 01:24:05,613
This place is amazing,

1739
01:24:06,113 --> 01:24:08,449
but Earth is...

1740
01:24:10,075 --> 01:24:11,076
home.

1741
01:24:12,369 --> 01:24:14,038
I didn't give it
a chance, but...

1742
01:24:15,748 --> 01:24:16,749
now...

1743
01:24:18,292 --> 01:24:19,293
I want to try.

1744
01:24:24,965 --> 01:24:25,966
With you.

1745
01:24:26,550 --> 01:24:27,635
[gasps]

1746
01:24:30,471 --> 01:24:31,639
Are you sure?

1747
01:24:34,350 --> 01:24:35,351
We're family.

1748
01:24:35,434 --> 01:24:37,937
[gasps, sighs]

1749
01:24:45,611 --> 01:24:46,904
This isn't goodbye.

1750
01:24:47,404 --> 01:24:49,823
It's just not yet.

1751
01:24:52,826 --> 01:24:53,994
We understand.

1752
01:24:55,746 --> 01:24:58,916
You are unique, Elio of Earth,

1753
01:24:58,999 --> 01:25:02,753
and "unique" can sometimes
feel like "alone."

1754
01:25:04,129 --> 01:25:06,465
But you are not alone.

1755
01:25:10,302 --> 01:25:11,303
Okay.

1756
01:25:11,804 --> 01:25:12,805
Bye.

1757
01:25:13,347 --> 01:25:14,348
I love you.

1758
01:25:20,729 --> 01:25:23,816
Okay. Bye.
[distorted] I love you.

1759
01:25:23,899 --> 01:25:25,985
[distorted] Okay. Bye.
I love you.

1760
01:25:26,068 --> 01:25:27,528
[ambassador speaking
alien language]

1761
01:25:28,237 --> 01:25:30,322
[distorted] Okay. Bye.
I love you.

1762
01:25:30,406 --> 01:25:32,032
[speaking alien language]

1763
01:25:37,288 --> 01:25:38,789
[growls]

1764
01:25:38,872 --> 01:25:40,624
[♪ Emotional music playing]

1765
01:25:40,708 --> 01:25:41,959
[growls]

1766
01:25:44,670 --> 01:25:45,671
I love you, too.

1767
01:25:56,432 --> 01:25:57,433
Let's go home.

1768
01:26:00,477 --> 01:26:02,479
[♪ Emotional music continues]

1769
01:26:09,987 --> 01:26:11,697
[spaceship whirs]

1770
01:26:37,598 --> 01:26:39,475
[narrator on recording]
<i>It's an ancient human theme.</i>

1771
01:26:39,558 --> 01:26:41,477
<i>You can find it
in virtually every culture.</i>

1772
01:26:41,560 --> 01:26:43,896
<i>In, uh, religion,
folklore, superstition,</i>

1773
01:26:43,979 --> 01:26:45,314
<i>and, now, in science.</i>

1774
01:26:46,732 --> 01:26:51,028
<i>The search for life elsewhere
is remarkable in our age</i>

1775
01:26:51,570 --> 01:26:52,946
<i>because this is the first time</i>

1776
01:26:53,030 --> 01:26:56,241
<i>that we can actually do
something besides speculation.</i>

1777
01:27:01,997 --> 01:27:04,750
<i>We can send spacecraft
to nearby planets.</i>

1778
01:27:06,293 --> 01:27:08,337
<i>We can use
large radio telescopes to see</i>

1779
01:27:08,420 --> 01:27:11,423
<i>if there is any message
being sent to us lately.</i>

1780
01:27:13,842 --> 01:27:17,513
<i>And it touches to
the deepest of human concerns.</i>

1781
01:27:18,389 --> 01:27:19,431
<i>Are we alone?</i>

1782
01:29:36,613 --> 01:29:38,615
[radio static,
frequency changing]

1783
01:29:44,496 --> 01:29:46,290
[growling through radio]

1784
01:29:46,957 --> 01:29:49,126
Glordon, your disc is muted.

1785
01:29:49,209 --> 01:29:50,294
[Glordon] <i>Oops, sorry.</i>

1786
01:29:50,377 --> 01:29:53,297
<i>Now, tell me everything.</i>

